Name: Bulbasaur
FlavorText: For some time after its birth, it grows by taking nourishment from the seed on its back.

Name: Bulbasaur
FlavorText: While it is young, it uses the nutrients that are stored in the seed on its back in order to grow.

Name: Bulbasaur
FlavorText: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

Name: Bulbasaur
FlavorText: It can go for days without eating a single morsel. In the bulb on its back, it stores energy.

Name: Bulbasaur
FlavorText: Bulbasaur can be seen napping in bright sunlight. There is a seed on its back. By soaking up the sun’s rays, the seed grows progressively larger.

Name: Bulbasaur
FlavorText: For some time after its birth, it grows by gaining nourishment from the seed on its back.

Name: Bulbasaur
FlavorText: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this Pokémon.

Name: Bulbasaur
FlavorText: It carries a seed on its back right from birth. As it grows older, the seed also grows larger.

Name: Bulbasaur
FlavorText: The seed on its back is filled with nutrients. The seed grows steadily larger as its body grows.

Name: Bulbasaur
FlavorText: While it is young, it uses the nutrients that are stored in the seeds on its back in order to grow.

Name: Ivysaur
FlavorText: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower’s coming bloom.

Name: Ivysaur
FlavorText: Exposure to sunlight adds to its strength. Sunlight also makes the bud on its back grow larger.

Name: Ivysaur
FlavorText: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

Name: Ivysaur
FlavorText: The bud on its back grows by drawing energy. It gives off an aroma when it is ready to bloom.

Name: Ivysaur
FlavorText: There is a bud on this Pokémon’s back. To support its weight, Ivysaur’s legs and trunk grow thick and strong. If it starts spending more time lying in the sunlight, it’s a sign that the bud will bloom into a large flower soon.

Name: Ivysaur
FlavorText: There is a plant bulb on its back. When it absorbs nutrients, the bulb is said to blossom into a large flower.

Name: Ivysaur
FlavorText: If the bud on its back starts to smell sweet, it is evidence that the large flower will soon bloom.

Name: Ivysaur
FlavorText: To support its bulb, IVYSAUR’s legs grow sturdy. If it spends more time lying in the sunlight, the bud will soon bloom into a large flower.

Name: Ivysaur
FlavorText: The bulb on its back grows as it absorbs nutrients. The bulb gives off a pleasant aroma when it blooms.

Name: Ivysaur
FlavorText: The bulb on its back grows by drawing energy. It gives off an aroma when it is ready to bloom.

Name: Venusaur
FlavorText: In order to support its flower, which has grown larger due to Mega Evolution, its back and legs have become stronger.

Name: Venusaur
FlavorText: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.

Name: Venusaur
FlavorText: A bewitching aroma wafts from its flower. The fragrance becalms those engaged in a battle.

Name: Venusaur
FlavorText: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

Name: Venusaur
FlavorText: The flower on its back catches the sun’s rays. The sunlight is then absorbed and used for energy.

Name: Venusaur
FlavorText: There is a large flower on Venusaur’s back. The flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and sunlight. The flower’s aroma soothes the emotions of people.

Name: Venusaur
FlavorText: By spreading the broad petals of its flower and catching the sun’s rays, it fills its body with power.

Name: Venusaur
FlavorText: It is able to convert sunlight into energy. As a result, it is more powerful in the summertime.

Name: Venusaur
FlavorText: VENUSAUR’s flower is said to take on vivid colors if it gets plenty of nutrition and sunlight. The flower’s aroma soothes the emotions of people.

Name: Venusaur
FlavorText: As it warms itself and absorbs the sunlight, its flower petals release a pleasant fragrance.

Name: Venusaur
FlavorText: The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If the Pokémon is healthy, its tail burns intensely.

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: The flame at the tip of its tail makes a sound as it burns. You can only hear it in quiet places.

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: The flame that burns at the tip of its tail is an indication of its emotions. The flame wavers when Charmander is enjoying itself. If the Pokémon becomes enraged, the flame burns fiercely.

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: The flame on its tail indicates Charmander’s life force. If it is healthy, the flame burns brightly.

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: The flame on its tail shows the strength of its life force. If it is weak, the flame also burns weakly.

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: The flame that burns at the tip of its tail is an indication of its emotions. The flame wavers when CHARMANDER is happy, and blazes when it is enraged.

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: If it’s healthy, the flame on the tip of its tail will burn vigorously, even if it gets a bit wet.

Name: Charmander
FlavorText: Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: Tough fights could excite this Pokémon. When excited, it may breathe out bluish-white flames.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: Charmeleon mercilessly destroys its foes using its sharp claws. If it encounters a strong foe, it turns aggressive. In this excited state, the flame at the tip of its tail flares with a bluish white color.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the air temperature to unbearably high levels.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: It lashes about with its tail to knock down its foe. It then tears up the fallen opponent with sharp claws.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: It is very hotheaded by nature, so it constantly seeks opponents. It calms down only when it wins.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: Without pity, its sharp claws destroy foes. If it encounters a strong enemy, it becomes agitated, and the flame on its tail flares with a bluish white color.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the air temperature to  unbearably high levels.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: Tough fights could excite this POKéMON. When excited, it may blow out bluish-white flames.

Name: Charmeleon
FlavorText: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: Its bond with its Trainer is the source of its power. It boasts speed and maneuverability greater than that of a jet fighter.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: The overwhelming power that fills its entire body causes it to turn black and create intense blue flames.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: The flame inside its body burns hotter than 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit. When Charizard roars, that temperature climbs even higher.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: This colossal, flame-winged figure of a Charizard was brought about by Gigantamax energy.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: It is said that Charizard’s fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: When this Pokémon expels a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tails burns more intensely.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: Charizard flies around the sky in search of powerful opponents. It breathes fire of such great heat that it melts anything. However, it never turns its fiery breath on any opponent weaker than itself.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: When expelling a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: Breathing intense, hot flames, it can melt almost anything. Its breath inflicts terrible pain on enemies.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: If CHARIZARD becomes furious, the flame at the tip of its tail flares up in a light blue shade.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: A CHARIZARD flies about in search of strong opponents. It breathes intense flames that can melt any material. However, it will never torch a weaker foe.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: It uses its wings to fly high. The temperature of its fire increases as it gains experience in battle.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: If CHARIZARD becomes furious, the flame at the tip of its tail flares up in a whitish-blue color.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: When expelling a blast of super hot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.

Name: Charizard
FlavorText: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: It hides in its shell to protect itself, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: When it feels threatened, it draws its limbs inside its shell and sprays water from its mouth.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: Shoots water at prey while in the water. Withdraws into its shell when in danger.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: Squirtle’s shell is not merely used for protection. The shell’s rounded shape and the grooves on its surface help minimize resistance in water, enabling this Pokémon to swim at high speeds.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: It shelters itself in its shell, then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: It shelters itself in its shell then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: The shell, which hardens soon after it is born, is resilient. If you poke it, it will bounce back out.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: The shell is soft when it is born. It soon becomes so resilient, prodding fingers will bounce off it.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: Its shell is not just for protection. Its rounded shape and the grooves on its surface minimize resistance in water, enabling SQUIRTLE to swim at high speeds.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. It powerfully sprays foam  from its mouth.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: When it feels threatened, it draws its legs inside its shell and sprays water from its mouth.

Name: Squirtle
FlavorText: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

Name: Wartortle
FlavorText: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.

Name: Wartortle
FlavorText: It cleverly controls its furry ears and tail to maintain its balance while swimming.

Name: Wartortle
FlavorText: It is recognized as a symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.

Name: Wartortle
FlavorText: When tapped on its head, this Pokémon will pull it in, but its tail will stick out a little bit.

Name: Wartortle
FlavorText: Its tail is large and covered with a rich, thick fur. The tail becomes increasingly deeper in color as Wartortle ages. The scratches on its shell are evidence of this Pokémon’s toughness as a battler.

Name: Wartortle
FlavorText: When tapped, this Pokémon will pull in its head, but its tail will still stick out a little bit.

Name: Wartortle
FlavorText: It is a well-established symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it, that WARTORTLE is very old.

Name: Wartortle
FlavorText: Its large tail is covered with rich, thick fur that deepens in color with age. The scratches on its shell are evidence of this POKéMON’s toughness in battle.

Name: Wartortle
FlavorText: It often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For fast swimming, it moves its ears to maintain balance.

Name: Wartortle
FlavorText: This POKéMON is very popular as a pet. Its fur-covered tail is a symbol of its longevity.

Name: Wartortle
FlavorText: Its long, furry tail is a symbol of longevity, making it quite popular among older people.

Name: Wartortle
FlavorText: Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.

Name: Blastoise
FlavorText: The cannon on its back is as powerful as a tank gun. Its tough legs and back enable it to withstand the recoil from firing the cannon.

Name: Blastoise
FlavorText: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.

Name: Blastoise
FlavorText: The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water capable of punching holes through thick steel.

Name: Blastoise
FlavorText: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

Name: Blastoise
FlavorText: Once it takes aim at its enemy, it blasts out water with even more force than a fire hose.

Name: Blastoise
FlavorText: Blastoise has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet.

Name: Blastoise
FlavorText: The pressurized water jets on this brutal Pokémon’s shell are used for high-speed tackles.

Name: Blastoise
FlavorText: It deliberately makes itself heavy so it can withstand the recoil of the water jets it fires.

Name: Blastoise
FlavorText: The waterspouts that protrude from its shell are highly accurate. Their bullets of water can precisely nail tin cans from a distance of over 160 feet.

Name: Blastoise
FlavorText: It firmly plants its feet on the ground before shooting water from the jets on its back.

Name: Blastoise
FlavorText: A brutal POKéMON with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: In its belly burns a fire, which Vulpix spits out in the form of fireballs. When young, this Pokémon has but one white tail. As the Pokémon matures, this single tail splits into six.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: It controls balls of fire. As it grows, its six tails split from their tips to make more tails.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: Both its fur and its tails are beautiful. As it grows, the tails split and form more tails.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: It manipulates balls of fire to catch its prey. If you raise one from when it’s young, it will grow close to you like a puppy Pokémon.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: Its beautiful tails have made it very popular. However, if it’s not brushed diligently, it will be a mass of tangles before you know it.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: From its mouth spew flames that seem to resemble the spirits of the deceased. Some people mistakenly think this fire is a ghost.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: Its beautiful fur and tails have made it very popular. As it grows, its tails split to form more tails.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: Inside Vulpix’s body burns a flame that never goes out. During the daytime, when the temperatures rise, this Pokémon releases flames from its mouth to prevent its body from growing too hot.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: At the time of its birth, Vulpix has one white tail. The tail separates into six if this Pokémon receives plenty of love from its Trainer. The six tails become magnificently curled.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: When it is born, it has just one snow-white tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: If it is attacked by an enemy that is stronger than itself, it feigns injury to fool the enemy and escapes.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: As it develops, its single white tail gains color and splits into six. It is quite warm and cuddly.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: It can freely control fire, making fiery orbs fly like will-o’-the-wisps. Just before evolution, its six tails grow hot  as if on fire.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: As its body grows larger, its six warm tails become more beautiful, with a more luxurious coat of fur.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: As it develops,  its single white tail gains color and splits into six. It is quite warm and cuddly.

Name: Vulpix
FlavorText: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: The coat of gleaming golden fur is quite magnificent. This species is said to store sacred power in its nine long tails and to live for a millennium.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Its nine tails are said to be imbued with a mystic power. The Pokémon is said to live for 1,000 years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1,000-year curse.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: According to an enduring legend, nine noble saints were united and reincarnated as this Pokémon.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: The flickering flames it spews from its mouth leave its opponents hypnotized. Then, this extremely intelligent Pokémon attacks.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It is vindictive and relentless by nature. Those who cross it even once will be cursed for a thousand years, along with their descendants.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Said to live for a thousand years, this Pokémon uses its supernatural abilities to manipulate fire. It can burn its prey to a crisp as it pleases.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Legend has it that this mystical Pokémon was formed when nine saints coalesced into one.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Legend has it that Ninetales came into being when nine wizards possessing sacred powers merged into one. This Pokémon is highly intelligent—it can understand human speech.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Ninetales casts a sinister light from its bright red eyes to gain total control over its foe’s mind. This Pokémon is said to live for a thousand years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It has nine long tails and fur that gleams gold. It is said to live for 1,000 years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Each of its nine tails is imbued with supernatural power, and it can live for a thousand years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Its nine tails are said to be imbued with a mystic power. It can live for a thousand years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Its nine beautiful tails are filled with a wondrous energy that could keep it alive for 1,000 years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Some legends claim that each of its nine tails has its own unique type of special mystical power.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It has long been said that each of the nine tails embody an enchanted power. A long-lived NINETALES will have fur that shines like gold.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It has nine long tails and fur that  gleams gold. It is said to live for  1,000 years.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Legend has it that NINETALES came into being when nine wizards possessing sacred powers merged into one. This POKéMON is highly intelligent - it can understand human speech.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: It is said to live a thousand years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: According to an enduring legend, 9 noble saints were united and reincarnated as this POKéMON.

Name: Ninetales
FlavorText: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: It may be mistaken for a clump of weeds. If you try to yank it out of the ground, it shrieks horribly.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: Oddish searches for fertile, nutrient-rich soil, then plants itself. During the daytime, while it is planted, this Pokémon’s feet are thought to change shape and become similar to the roots of trees.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: During the daytime, Oddish buries itself in soil to absorb nutrients from the ground using its entire body. The more fertile the soil, the glossier its leaves become.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: Its scientific name is “Oddium Wanderus.” At night, it is said to walk nearly 1,000 feet on its two roots.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: Awakened by moonlight, it roams actively at night. In the day, it stays quietly underground.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: This POKéMON grows by absorbing moonlight. During the daytime, it buries itself in the ground, leaving only its leaves exposed to avoid detection by its enemies.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: During the daytime, ODDISH buries itself in soil to absorb nutrients from  the ground using its entire body. The more fertile the soil, the glossier its leaves become.

Name: Oddish
FlavorText: Awakened by moonlight, it roams  actively at night. In the day, it stays quietly underground.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: The nectar it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious that it can make noses curl from more than a mile away.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: Smells incredibly foul! However, around one out of a thousand people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: From its mouth Gloom drips honey that smells absolutely horrible. Apparently, it loves the horrid stench. It sniffs the noxious fumes and then drools even more of its honey.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: Gloom releases a foul fragrance from the pistil of its flower. When faced with danger, the stench worsens. If this Pokémon is feeling calm and secure, it does not release its usual stinky aroma.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: It secretes a sticky, drool-like honey. Although sweet, it smells too repulsive to get very close.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: A horribly noxious honey drools from its mouth. One whiff of the honey can result in memory loss. Some fans are said to enjoy this overwhelming stink, however.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn’t drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: From its mouth GLOOM drips honey that smells absolutely horrible. Apparently, it loves the horrid stench. It sniffs the noxious fumes and then  drools even more of its honey.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: The smell from its drool-like syrup and the pollen on its petals is so bad, it may make opponents faint.

Name: Gloom
FlavorText: Smells incredibly foul! However, around 1 out of 1,000 people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: It has the world’s largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: Flaps its broad flower petals to scatter its poisonous pollen. The flapping sound is very loud.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: Vileplume has the world’s largest petals. They are used to attract prey that are then doused with toxic spores. Once the prey are immobilized, this Pokémon catches and devours them.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: Vileplume’s toxic pollen triggers atrocious allergy attacks. That’s why it is advisable never to approach any attractive flowers in a jungle, however pretty they may be.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: The bud bursts into bloom with a bang. It then starts scattering allergenic, poisonous pollen.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: In seasons when it produces more pollen, the air around a VILEPLUME turns yellow with the powder as it walks. The pollen is highly toxic and causes paralysis.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: Its petals are the largest in the world. It fiendishly scatters allergy-causing pollen from its petals.

Name: Vileplume
FlavorText: By shaking its big petals, it scatters toxic pollen into the air, turning the air yellow.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Sometimes seen at the foot of trees in humid forests. The mushrooms on its back—called tochukaso—are not present on infant specimens and instead emerge as Paras matures.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Mushrooms named tochukaso grow on its back. They grow along with the host Paras.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Whether it’s due to a lack of moisture or a lack of nutrients, in Alola the mushrooms on Paras don’t grow up quite right.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Mushrooms called tochukaso sprout from its back. They can be dried and powdered to make a medicine used to extend life.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: No matter how much it eats, the mushrooms growing on its back steal away most of the nutrients it consumes.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Paras has parasitic mushrooms growing on its back called tochukaso. They grow large by drawing nutrients from this Bug Pokémon host. They are highly valued as a medicine for extending life.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Growing out of the bug’s back are mushrooms called tochukaso. The mushrooms grow with the bug host.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: As its body grows, large mushrooms named tochukaso start sprouting out of its back.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: It is doused with mushroom spores when it is born. As its body grows, mushrooms sprout from its back.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: A PARAS has parasitic tochukaso mushrooms growing on its back. They grow by drawing nutrients from the host. They are valued as a medicine for long life.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by drawing nutrients from the bug host.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: PARAS has parasitic mushrooms growing on its back called tochukaso. They grow large by drawing nutrients from the BUG POKéMON host. They are highly valued as a medicine for extending life.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: The tochukaso growing on this POKéMON’s back orders it to extract juice from tree trunks.

Name: Paras
FlavorText: As its body grows large, oriental mushrooms named tochukaso start sprouting out of its back.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: Mushroom-lacking specimens of this Pokémon lie unmoving in the forest, lending credence to the hypothesis that the large mushroom is in control of Parasect’s actions.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: It is controlled by the mushroom, which has grown larger than the bug body. It is said to prefer damp places.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: Parasect is controlled by a mushroom that has grown larger than its host’s body. The Pokémon scatters poisonous spores.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushrooms on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: Its poisonous spores are also used in traditional medicine. Apparently, spores produced in Alola are not of very good quality.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: The bug is mostly dead, with the mushroom on its back having become the main body. If the mushroom comes off, the bug stops moving.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: It scatters toxic spores from its mushroom cap. Once harvested, these spores can be steeped and boiled down to prepare herbal medicines.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: The large mushroom on its back controls it. It often fights over territory with Shiinotic.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: Parasect is known to infest large trees en masse and drain nutrients from the lower trunk and roots. When an infested tree dies, they move onto another tree all at once.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: The larger the mushroom on its back grows, the stronger the mushroom spores it scatters.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: A mushroom grown larger than the host’s body controls Parasect. It scatters poisonous spores.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: It stays mostly in dark, damp places, the preference not of the bug, but of the big mushroom on its back.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: It is controlled by a mushroom grown larger than the bug body. It is said to prefer damp places.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: PARASECT are known to infest the roots of large trees en masse and drain nutrients. When an infested tree dies, they move onto another tree all at once.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: It scatters toxic spores from the mushroom cap. In China, the spores are used as herbal medicine.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: When nothing’s left to extract from the bug, the mushrooms on its back leave spores on the bug’s egg.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: It stays mostly in dark, damp places, the preference not of the bug, but of the big mushrooms on its back.

Name: Parasect
FlavorText: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushrooms on its back. They appear to do all the thinking.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: If its chronic headache peaks, it may exhibit odd powers. It seems unable to recall such an episode.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Suffers perpetual headaches. If the agony grows too great, Psyduck’s latent power erupts, contrary to Psyduck’s intent. Ergo, I am exploring ways to ease the pain.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: It never remembers using its odd powers, so it always tilts its head in puzzlement.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: If its usual headache worsens, it starts exhibiting odd powers. It can’t remember doing so, however.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: As Psyduck gets stressed out, its headache gets progressively worse. It uses intense psychic energy to overwhelm those around it.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Psyduck is constantly beset by headaches. If the Pokémon lets its strange power erupt, apparently the pain subsides for a while.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Always tormented by headaches. It uses psychic powers, but whether it intends to do so is not known.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: It has been found that its brain cells are 10 times more active when Psyduck is experiencing a headache.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Using psychokinesis gives it a headache, so it normally passes the time spacing out and doing as little as possible.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: This Pokémon is troubled by constant headaches. The more pain it’s in, the more powerful its psychokinesis becomes.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: As a result of headaches so fierce they cause it to cry, it sometimes uses psychokinesis without meaning to.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: If it uses its mysterious power, Psyduck can’t remember having done so. It apparently can’t form a memory of such an event because it goes into an altered state that is much like deep sleep.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Psyduck uses a mysterious power. When it does so, this Pokémon generates brain waves that are supposedly only seen in sleepers. This discovery spurred controversy among scholars.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: It has mystical powers but doesn’t recall that it has used them. That is why it always looks puzzled.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: When headaches stimulate its brain cells, which are usually inactive, it can use a mysterious power.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Overwhelmed by enigmatic abilities, it suffers a constant headache. It sometimes uses mysterious powers.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: When its headache intensifies, it starts using strange powers. However, it has no recollection of its powers, so it always looks befuddled and bewildered.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily POKéMON will use psychokinetic powers.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: PSYDUCK uses a mysterious power. When it does so, this POKéMON  generates brain waves that are supposedly only seen in sleepers. This discovery spurred controversy among scholars.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: The only time it can use its psychic power is when its sleeping brain cells happen to wake.

Name: Psyduck
FlavorText: Always tormented by headaches. It uses psychic powers, but it is not known if it intends to do so.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: It swims gracefully along on the quiet, slow-moving rivers and lakes of which it is so fond.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: When it swims at full speed using its long, webbed limbs, its forehead somehow begins to glow.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Its body is strong, and it has webbing on its hands and feet. Golduck can swim easily through rough seas, clawing its way through the high waves.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: The flippers of its well-developed limbs give it shocking speed. It is the best swimmer among Pokémon.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in lakes. It swims faster than any world-class swimmer.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Old tales tell of Golduck punishing those that defiled its river. The guilty were dragged into the water and taken away.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in gently flowing rivers. It paddles through the water with its long limbs, putting its graceful swimming skills on display.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Its long, slim limbs end in broad flippers. They are used for swimming gracefully in lakes.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: A professional swimmer, it can continue swimming for two days straight by waving its long tail skillfully.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Even fast-swimming fish Pokémon can be disabled by Golduck. It brings them to a standstill and seizes them.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: It swims along the banks of lakes and catches fish Pokémon. It takes them to the shore and quietly eats them up.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: It is said that the red part of its forehead grants supernatural powers to those who possess one, so it was over-hunted in the past.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Golduck is the fastest swimmer among all Pokémon. It swims effortlessly, even in a rough, stormy sea. It sometimes rescues people from wrecked ships floundering in high seas.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: The webbed flippers on its forelegs and hind legs and the streamlined body of Golduck give it frightening speed. This Pokémon is definitely much faster than even the most athletic swimmer.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: The forelegs are webbed, helping to make it an adept swimmer. It can be seen swimming elegantly in lakes, etc.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: It appears by waterways at dusk. It may use telekinetic powers if its forehead glows mysteriously.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: When its forehead shines mysteriously, Golduck can use the full extent of its power.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: It is seen swimming dynamically and elegantly using its well-developed limbs and flippers.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: A Pokémon that lives in lakes. It swims faster than any human swimming champion.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: A GOLDUCK is an adept swimmer. It sometimes joins competitive swimmers in training. It uses psychic powers when its forehead shimmers with light.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Often seen swimming elegantly by lakeshores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster Kappa.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Its slim and long limbs end in broad flippers. They are used for swimming gracefully in lakes.

Name: Golduck
FlavorText: Often seen swimming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: They patrol their territory in pairs. I believe the igneous rock components in the fur of this species are the result of volcanic activity in its habitat.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It’s very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It is a Pokémon with a loyal nature. It will remain motionless until it is given an order by its Trainer.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: Extremely loyal, it will fearlessly bark at any opponent to protect its own Trainer from harm.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: A Pokémon with a friendly nature. However, it will bark fiercely at anything invading its territory.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It has lived alongside humans since ages ago. Its bones have been found in excavations of ruins from the Stone Age.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: While it’s quite friendly toward humans once it’s grown used to them, in the wild it must be quite fierce to defend its territory from Rockruff.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It looks cute, but when you approach another Trainer’s Growlithe, it will bark at you and bite.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It’s both clever and loyal, but if a stranger tries to invade its territory, it barks threateningly.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: Growlithe has a superb sense of smell. Once it smells anything, this Pokémon won’t forget the scent, no matter what. It uses its advanced olfactory sense to determine the emotions of other living things.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: Very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: Extremely loyal to its Trainer, it will bark at those who approach the Trainer unexpectedly and run them out of town.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: A Pokémon with a loyal nature. It will remain motionless until it is given an order by its Trainer.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: Its superb sense of smell ensures that this POKéMON won’t forget any scent, no matter what. It uses its sense of smell to detect the emotions of others.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It is very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: It controls a big territory. If it detects an unknown smell, it roars loudly to force out the intruder.

Name: Growlithe
FlavorText: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: Snaps at its foes with fangs cloaked in blazing flame. Despite its bulk, it deftly feints every which way, leading opponents on a deceptively merry chase as it all but dances around them.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can’t help but grovel before it.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: Its proud and regal appearance has captured the hearts of people since long ago.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: A Pokémon that has long been admired for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: A legendary Pokémon in the East. Many people are charmed by the grace and beauty of its running.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: There are so many old tales about them that they’re called legendary Pokémon, but there are way more of them around than you’d expect.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: Legends tell of its fighting alongside a general and conquering a whole country.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: The fire burning inside its body serves as the energy to fuel it as it runs great distances. It appears in many legends.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: Overflowing with beauty and majesty, this strong Pokémon appears in ancient Eastern folklore.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: Arcanine is known for its high speed. It is said to be capable of running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within this Pokémon’s body is its source of power.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: This legendary Chinese Pokémon is considered magnificent. Many people are enchanted by its grand mane.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: This fleet-footed POKéMON is said to run over 6,200 miles in a single day and night. The fire that blazes wildly within its body is its source of power.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: A POKéMON that is described in Chinese legends. It is said to race at an unbelievable speed.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were attracted to its movement as it ran through prairies.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: This legendary Chinese POKEMON is considered magnificent. Many people are enchanted by its grand mane.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: A legendary POKéMON in China. Many people are charmed by its grace and beauty while running.

Name: Arcanine
FlavorText: A POKéMON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: In rivers with fast-flowing water, this Pokémon will cling to a rock by using its thick lips, which act like a suction cup.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokémon’s innards showing through the skin.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: The direction of the spiral on the belly differs by area. It is more adept at swimming than walking.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: The direction of the swirl on their stomachs differs depending on where they live. Poliwag aficionados can tell them apart at a glance.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Despite the danger, it wants to come up on land. So it does its best to waddle along, but when an enemy finds it, it rushes back to the water.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: It’s still not very good at walking. Its Trainers should train this Pokémon to walk every day.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: The swirl on its belly is its internal organs showing through. If the swirl is tinged white, that means it’s affected by some disease.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Poliwag has a very thin skin. It is possible to see the Pokémon’s spiral innards right through the skin. Despite its thinness, however, the skin is also very flexible. Even sharp fangs bounce right off it.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Its slick black skin is thin and damp. A part of its internal organs can be seen through the skin as a spiral pattern.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: The direction of its belly spiral differs by area. The equator is thought to have an effect on this.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Because it is inept at walking on its newly grown legs, it always  swims around in water.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: It is possible to see this POKéMON’s spiral innards right through its thin skin. However, the skin is also very flexible. Even sharp fangs bounce right off it.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Its newly grown legs prevent it from walking well. It appears to prefer swimming over walking.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: The swirl on its belly is its insides showing through the skin. It looks clearer after it eats.

Name: Poliwag
FlavorText: Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s sweat is a slimy mucus. When captured, Poliwhirl can slither from its enemies’ grasp and escape.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl’s has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Under attack, it uses its belly spiral to put the foe to sleep. It then makes its escape.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Its health suffers when its skin dries out, so be sure to moisturize it diligently.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Although it has become capable of living on land, it spends its time in the water, where its prey, fish Pokémon, are plentiful.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: It marches over the land in search of bug Pokémon to eat. Then it takes them underwater so it can dine on them where it’s safe.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Although it can live on land, it prefers to stay in the water, where it has fewer natural enemies.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: The surface of Poliwhirl’s body is always wet and slick with a slimy fluid. Because of this slippery covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Its two legs are well developed. Even though it can live on the ground, it prefers living in water.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: It can live in or out of water. When out of water, it constantly sweats to keep its body slimy.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: The skin on most of its body is moist. However, the skin on its belly spiral feels smooth.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: The swirl on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it may gradually cause drowsiness.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Its body surface is always wet and slick with an oily fluid. Because of this greasy covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: The surface of POLIWHIRL’s body is always wet and slick with an oily fluid. Because of this greasy covering, it can easily slip and slide out of the clutches of any enemy in battle.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Though it is skilled at walking, it prefers to live underwater where there is less danger.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Under attack, it uses its belly  spiral to put the foe to sleep. It then makes its escape.

Name: Poliwhirl
FlavorText: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: With its extremely tough muscles, it could keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Poliwrath is skilled at both swimming and martial arts. It uses its well-trained arms to dish out powerful punches.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas, Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Swims powerfully using all the muscles in its body. It can even overtake world-class swimmers.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: The muscles it has developed through swimming are thick and powerful. When it lands a square punch, it can turn huge boulders to dust.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: It’s quite a gifted swimmer, even among Water-type Pokémon, but it normally spends its time on land.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Its percentage of body fat is nearly zero. Its body is entirely muscle, which makes it heavy and forces its swimming prowess to develop.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Poliwrath in the Alola region are strong swimmers that use the breaststroke. Many children learn to swim by imitating Poliwrath.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Poliwrath’s highly developed, brawny muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. It is so tirelessly strong, this Pokémon can swim back and forth across the ocean without effort.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: A swimmer adept at both the front crawl and breaststroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: With its extremely tough muscles, it can keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Although an energetic, skilled swimmer that uses all of its muscles, it lives on dry land.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: This strong and skilled swimmer is even capable of crossing the Pacific Ocean just by kicking.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Its highly developed muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. This POKéMON can swim back and forth across the Pacific Ocean without effort.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: An adept swimmer, it knows the front crawl, butterfly, and more. It is faster than the best human swimmers.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: POLIWRATH’s highly developed, brawny muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. It is so tirelessly strong, this POKéMON can swim back and forth across the Pacific Ocean without effort.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: It can use its well-developed arms and legs to run on the surface of the water for a split second.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: Swims powerfully using all the muscles in its body. It can even overtake champion swimmers.

Name: Poliwrath
FlavorText: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares tiny bugs with its vines and devours them.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: Bellsprout’s thin and flexible body lets it bend and sway to avoid any attack, however strong it may be. From its mouth, this Pokémon spits a corrosive fluid that melts even iron.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: Even though its body is extremely skinny, it is blindingly fast when catching its prey.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: It plants its feet deep underground to replenish water. It can’t escape its enemy while it’s rooted.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: A BELLSPROUT’s thin and flexible body lets it bend and sway to avoid any attack, however strong it may be. From its mouth, it leaks a fluid that melts even iron.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: A carnivorous POKéMON that traps and eats bugs. It appears to use its root feet to replenish moisture.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: If it notices anything that moves, it immediately flings its vine at the object.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares tiny insects with its vines and devours them.

Name: Bellsprout
FlavorText: A carnivorous POKéMON that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: This Pokémon has the appearance of a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: When hungry, it swallows anything that moves. Its hapless prey is dissolved by strong acids.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: Weepinbell has a large hook on its rear end. At night, the Pokémon hooks on to a tree branch and goes to sleep. If it moves around in its sleep, it may wake up to find itself on the ground.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: The leafy parts act as cutters for slashing foes. It spits a fluid that dissolves everything.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: A Pokémon that appears to be a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: If its prey is bigger than its mouth, it slices up the victim with sharp leaves, then eats every morsel.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: Even though it is filled with acid, it does not melt because it also oozes a protective fluid.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: At night, a WEEPINBELL hangs on to a tree branch with its hooked rear and sleeps. If it moves around in its sleep, it may wake up to find itself on the ground.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: When it’s hungry, it swings its razor-sharp leaves, slicing up any unlucky object nearby for food.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: Even though it is filled with ACID, it does not melt because it also oozes a neutralizing fluid.

Name: Weepinbell
FlavorText: When hungry, it swallows anything that moves. Its hapless prey is melted inside by strong acids.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: In its mouth, it pools a fragrant nectar-like fluid. The fluid is really an acid that dissolves anything.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is dissolved in a day, bones and all.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Victreebel has a long vine that extends from its head. This vine is waved and flicked about as if it were an animal to attract prey. When an unsuspecting prey draws near, this Pokémon swallows it whole.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Once ingested into this Pokémon’s body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: It pools in its mouth a fluid with a honey-like scent, which is really an acid that dissolves anything.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: It pools in its mouth a fluid with a honeylike scent, which is really an acid that dissolves anything.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: This horrifying plant Pokémon attracts prey with aromatic honey, then melts them in its mouth.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Acid that has dissolved many prey becomes sweeter, making it even more effective at attracting prey.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: The long vine extending from its head is waved about as if it were a living thing to attract prey. When an unsuspecting victim approaches, it is swallowed whole.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Lures prey into its mouth with a honeylike aroma. The helpless prey is melted with a dissolving fluid.

Name: Victreebel
FlavorText: Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is melted in a day, bones and all.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: They fire beams from the glassy, magenta orbs that resemble eyes atop their heads, and they drift in shallow seas. During low tide, they can sometimes be found on beaches, desiccated.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: It drifts in sea currents. Countless fishers are hurt by its poison stingers.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Its body is mostly composed of water. It shoots strange beams from its crystal-like eyes.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: This Pokémon is mostly made of water. A Tentacool out in the ocean is very hard to spot, because its body blends in with the sea.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Tentacool is not a particularly strong swimmer. It drifts across the surface of shallow seas as it searches for prey.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: It can sometimes be found all dry and shriveled up on a beach. Toss it back into the sea to revive it.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Its body is 99% water. The remaining 1% contains the organ that makes its poison.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: It drifts through the sea searching for prey. Its poisonous tentacles break off sometimes, but after a while, they grow back.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: It drifts in shallow seas, such as the areas near beaches. If you get bitten or stabbed by its toxic tentacles, rush to the hospital.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: They can be found lying dehydrated on beaches, but they are often still alive. When soaked in water, they will revive.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Tentacool absorbs sunlight and refracts it using water inside its body to convert it into beam energy. This Pokémon shoots beams from the small round organ above its eyes.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Tentacool’s body is largely composed of water. If it is removed from the sea, it dries up like parchment. If this Pokémon happens to become dehydrated, put it back into the sea.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by their stingers.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Its body is virtually composed of water. It shoots strange beams from its crystal-like eyes.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Because its body is almost entirely composed of water, it shrivels up if it is washed ashore.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: It drifts aimlessly in waves. Very difficult to see in water, it may not be noticed until it stings.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: When the tide goes out, dehydrated TENTACOOL remains can be found washed up on the shore.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: It drifts in sea currents. Countless fishermen are hurt by its poison stingers.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Its body is almost entirely composed of water. It ensnares its foe with its two long tentacles, then stabs with the poison stingers at their tips.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Its eyes are as transparent as crystals. From them, it shoots mysterious beams of light.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: TENTACOOL absorbs sunlight and refracts it using water inside its body to convert it into beam energy. This POKéMON shoots beams from its crystal-like eyes.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: As it floats along on the waves, it uses its toxic feelers to stab anything it touches.

Name: Tentacool
FlavorText: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It has 80 tentacles, each with a venomous tip. These tentacles are also extendible, lengthening when Tentacruel attempts to catch prey. Use caution.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It alerts others to danger by stridently flashing the red orbs on its head.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: With 80 tentacles for ensnaring victims, it prevents escape until the prey is weakened by poison.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Its 80 tentacles can stretch and shrink freely. Tentacruel ensnares prey in a net of spread-out tentacles, delivering venomous stings to its catch.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: When the red orbs on Tentacruel’s head glow brightly, watch out. The Pokémon is about to fire off a burst of ultrasonic waves.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Its 80 tentacles can stretch and contract freely. They wrap around prey and weaken it with poison.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It communicates with others of its kind by lighting up the red orbs on its head. When the orbs are blinking, it’s a warning sign.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It fires off ultrasonic waves from its red orbs to weaken its prey, and then it wraps them up in its 80 tentacles.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Although these Pokémon are rare, when a large outbreak of them occurs, all fish Pokémon disappear from the surrounding sea.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Normally, it has 80 poisonous tentacles. The longer one has been alive, the fewer tentacles it will have.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Tentacruel has tentacles that can be freely elongated and shortened at will. It ensnares prey with its tentacles and weakens the prey by dosing it with a harsh toxin. It can catch up to 80 prey at the same time.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Tentacruel has large red orbs on its head. The orbs glow before lashing the vicinity with a harsh ultrasonic blast. This Pokémon’s outburst creates rough waves around it.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It has 80 tentacles that move about freely. They can sting, causing poisoning and sharp, stabbing pain.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It extends its 80 tentacles to form an encircling poisonous net that is difficult to escape.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: In battle, it extends all 80 of its tentacles to entrap its opponent inside a poisonous net.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: Its 80 tentacles absorb water and stretch almost endlessly to constrict its prey and enemies.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: It lives in complex rock formations on the ocean floor and traps prey using its 80 tentacles. Its red orbs glow when it grows excited or agitated.

Name: Tentacruel
FlavorText: When its 80 feelers absorb water, it stretches to become like a net to entangle its prey.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: These Pokémon live in herds out in the grassland. Newborn foals lack their fiery manes, which will develop about an hour after birth.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its legs grow strong while it chases after its parents. It runs all day in fields and on mountains.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: About an hour after birth, Ponyta’s fiery mane and tail grow out, giving the Pokémon an impressive appearance.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: If you’ve been accepted by Ponyta, its burning mane is mysteriously no longer hot to the touch.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: It can’t run properly when it’s newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Capable of jumping incredibly high. Its hooves and sturdy legs absorb the impact of a hard landing.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Ponyta is very weak at birth. It can barely stand up. This Pokémon becomes stronger by stumbling and falling to keep up with its parent.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its legs grow strong while it chases after its parent. It runs in fields and mountains all day.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: As a newborn, it can barely stand. However, through galloping, its legs are made tougher and faster.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its hind legs, which have hooves that are harder than diamond, kick back at any presence it senses behind it.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: It is a weak runner immediately after birth. It gradually becomes faster by chasing after its parents.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: About an hour after birth, its fiery mane and tail grow out, giving it an impressive appearance.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: A PONYTA is very weak at birth. It can barely stand up. Its legs become stronger as it stumbles and falls while trying to keep up with its parent.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its hooves are ten times harder than diamond. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its body is light, and its legs are incredibly powerful. It can clear Ayers Rock in one leap.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Training by jumping over grass that grows longer every day has made it a world-class jumper.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its hind legs, which have harder-than-diamond hooves, kick back at any presence it senses behind it.

Name: Ponyta
FlavorText: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: Fiery mane aglow, Rapidash darts like an arrow across the land. This prodigiously swift creature can traverse the vast region of Hisui in a day and a half.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: It has astounding acceleration. From a standstill, it can reach top speed within 10 steps.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: The fastest runner becomes the leader, and it decides the herd’s pace and direction of travel.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: Just loves to run. If it sees something faster than itself, it will give chase at top speed.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: Rapidash usually can be seen casually cantering in the fields and plains. However, when this Pokémon turns serious, its fiery manes flare and blaze as it gallops its way up to 150 mph.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: Very competitive, this Pokémon will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: When at an all-out gallop, its blazing mane sparkles, enhancing its beautiful appearance.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: With incredible acceleration, it reaches its top speed of 150 mph after running just 10 steps.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: At full gallop, its four hooves barely touch the ground because it moves so incredibly fast.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: It usually canters casually in the fields and plains. But once a RAPIDASH turns serious, its fiery manes flare and blaze as it gallops its way up to 150 mph.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: It can gallop at a top speed of 150 miles per hour. It can race as fast as a bullet train while ablaze.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: It just loves to gallop. The faster it goes, the longer the swaying flames of its mane will become.

Name: Rapidash
FlavorText: With incredible acceleration, it reaches its top speed of 150 mph after running just ten steps.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: When this Pokémon’s tail is soaked in water, sweetness seeps from it. Slowpoke uses this trait to lure in and fish up other Pokémon.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Slow-witted and oblivious, this Pokémon won’t feel any pain if its tail gets eaten. It won’t notice when its tail grows back, either.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Incredibly slow and sluggish. It is quite content to loll about without worrying about the time.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Although their tails, which fall off naturally, can easily be found lying around, they’re a precious ingredient for cooking.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: There are some places where Slowpoke is worshiped because of a long-standing belief that whenever Slowpoke yawns, it rains.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Alolan home cooking involves drying Slowpoke tails and then simmering them into a salty stew.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Its long tail often breaks off. It doesn’t really feel any pain, though, and the tail grows back, so Slowpoke isn’t particularly bothered.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Slowpoke uses its tail to catch prey by dipping it in water at the side of a river. However, this Pokémon often forgets what it’s doing and often spends entire days just loafing at water’s edge.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: It lazes vacantly near water. If something bites its tail, it won’t even notice for a whole day.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: A sweet sap leaks from its tail’s tip. Although not nutritious, the tail is pleasant to chew on.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: It catches prey by dipping its tail in water at the side of a river. But it often forgets what it is doing and spends entire days just loafing at water’s edge.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: It is always so absent-minded that it won’t react, even if its flavorful tail is bitten.

Name: Slowpoke
FlavorText: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Under the influence of Shellder’s digestive fluids, Slowpoke has awakened, gaining a great deal of power—and a little motivation to boot.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Having been swallowed whole by Shellder, Slowbro now has an iron defense. It’s pretty comfortable in there, too.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Tremendous energy strengthened the power of the Shellder on its tail, but it doesn’t really affect Slowpoke.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: When bathed in the energy of Mega Evolution, Shellder converts into impregnable armor. There is virtually no change in Slowpoke.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: All the energy from Mega Evolution poured into the Shellder on its tail, leaving Slowpoke to be swallowed whole.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: If the tail-biting Shellder is thrown off in a harsh battle, this Pokémon reverts to being an ordinary Slowpoke.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Though usually dim-witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Being bitten by a Shellder shocked this Pokémon into standing on two legs. If the Shellder lets go, it seems Slowbro will turn back into a Slowpoke.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Slowpoke became Slowbro when a Shellder bit on to its tail. Sweet flavors seeping from the tail make the Shellder feel as if its life is a dream.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Lives lazily by the sea. If the Shellder on its tail comes off, it becomes a Slowpoke again.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Shellder, in its greed to suck out more and more sweetness from Slowbro’s tail, has metamorphosed into a spiral-shaped shell.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Spacing out is basically all it does. It turns back into Slowpoke if its tail, along with Shellder, breaks off.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Whenever Shellder bites down hard on its tail, it gives Slowbro a flash of inspiration...which it forgets a moment later.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: It spaces out while gazing at the sea. With Shellder’s poison flowing through its body, it becomes even spacier.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Slowbro’s tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can’t be used for fishing anymore. This causes Slowbro to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: An attached Shellder won’t let go because of the tasty flavor that oozes out of its tail.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Naturally dull to begin with, it lost its ability to feel pain due to SHELLDER’s seeping poison.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: If the tail-biting SHELLDER is thrown off in a harsh battle, it reverts to being an ordinary SLOWPOKE.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: Its tail has a SHELLDER firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can’t be used for fishing anymore. This forces it to reluctantly swim and catch prey.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: The SHELLDER that latches onto SLOWPOKE’s tail is said to feed on the host’s leftover scraps.

Name: Slowbro
FlavorText: The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE’s tail is said to feed on the host’s left over scraps.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives on icebergs. It uses the sharp point on its head to break up ice as it swims in the sea.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Loves freezing-cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid climate of around 14 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Thanks to its thick fat, cold seas don’t bother it at all, but it gets tired pretty easily in warm waters.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: It has always been supposed that Seel live only in cold seas. Their having shown up in Alola is a mystery.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Seel hunts for prey in the frigid sea underneath sheets of ice. When it needs to breathe, it punches a hole through the ice with the sharply protruding section of its head.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Covered with light blue fur, its hide is thick and tough. It is active in bitter cold of -40 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: A Pokémon that lives on icebergs. It swims in the sea using the point on its head to break up ice.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: The colder it gets, the better it feels. It joyfully swims around oceans so cold that they are filled with floating ice.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: In daytime, it is often found asleep on the seabed in shallow waters. Its nostrils close while it swims.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Although it can’t walk well on land, it is a graceful swimmer. It especially loves being in frigid seas.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: SEEL hunt for prey in frigid, ice-covered seas. When it needs to breathe, it punches a hole through the ice with the sharply protruding section of its head.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick icebergs.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Covered with light blue fur, its hide is thick and tough. It is active in bitter cold of minus 40 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: The light blue fur that covers it keeps it protected against the cold. It loves iceberg-filled oceans.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: Loves freezing cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid climate of around 14F degrees.

Name: Seel
FlavorText: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: In snow, the pure white coat covering its body obscures it from predators.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: It sunbathes on the beach after meals. The rise in its body temperature helps its digestion.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: It swims through the ocean at a speed of eight knots, searching for Pokémon that will become its prey. It’s especially fond of Wishiwashi.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Dewgong loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this Pokémon sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Its streamlined body has little drag in water. The colder the temperature, the friskier it gets.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Its body is covered with a pure white fur. The colder the weather, the more active it becomes.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Its streamlined body has low resistance, and it swims around cold oceans at a speed of eight knots.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: It loves frigid seas with ice floes. It uses its long tail to change swimming direction quickly.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: It loves to snooze on bitterly cold ice. The sight of this POKéMON sleeping on a glacier was mistakenly thought to be a mermaid by a mariner long ago.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: It stores thermal energy in the body. It swims at a steady eight knots even in intensely cold waters.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: It sleeps under shallow ocean waters during the day, then looks for food at night when it’s cold.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Its entire body is a snowy-white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.

Name: Dewgong
FlavorText: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: Clamping on to an opponent reveals its vulnerable parts, so it uses this move only as a last resort.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: It swims backward by opening and closing its two shells. Its large tongue is always kept hanging out.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: It swims facing backward by opening and closing its two-piece shell. It is surprisingly fast.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: The shell can withstand any attack. However, when it is open, the tender body is exposed.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: Even when its shell is closed, its tongue still hangs out. If you give its tongue a good yank, the shock will cause Shellder to open its shell.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: The sand that accumulates inside its shell eventually becomes a pearl. But the pearl gets in the way, so it spits it out and discards it.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s tongue is always hanging out. It uses its tongue with great dexterity to dig up sand from the seabed in its search for food.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: The hardness of its shell surpasses the hardness of a diamond. In days gone by, people used the shells to make shields.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: At night, this Pokémon uses its broad tongue to burrow a hole in the seafloor sand and then sleep in it. While it is sleeping, Shellder closes its shell, but leaves its tongue hanging out.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: Grains of sand trapped in its shells mix with its body fluids to form beautiful pearls.

Name: Shellder
FlavorText: At night, it burrows a hole in the seafloor with its broad tongue to make a place to sleep. While asleep, it closes its shell, but leaves its tongue hanging out.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: When attacked, it launches its spikes in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: It fights by keeping its shell tightly shut for protection and by shooting spikes to repel foes.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Once it slams its shell shut, it is impossible to open, even by those with superior strength.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: For protection, it uses its harder-than-diamonds shell. It also shoots spikes from the shell.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Slowpoke tails are its favorite food. It has even been known to come up on land to look for Slowpoke from time to time.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: If areas of Cloyster’s very hard shell get damaged, those areas swell, gradually growing into large sharp spikes.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Excavation of the tombs of ancient hunting tribes has turned up many spears tipped with spikes that had fallen off this Pokémon’s shell.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Its hard shell cannot be shattered—not even by a bomb. The contents of the shell remain unknown.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Cloyster is capable of swimming in the sea. It does so by swallowing water, then jetting it out toward the rear. This Pokémon shoots spikes from its shell using the same system.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: It swims in the sea by swallowing water, then jetting it out toward the rear. The CLOYSTER shoots spikes from its shell using the same system.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

Name: Cloyster
FlavorText: Even a missile can’t break the spikes it uses to stab opponents. They’re even harder than its shell.

Name: Krabby
