FlavorText: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are lost in battle.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: Its pincers are superb weapons. They sometimes break off during battle, but they grow back fast.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: Krabby live on beaches, burrowed inside holes dug into the sand. On sandy beaches with little in the way of food, these Pokémon can be seen squabbling with each other over territory.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are broken in battle.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: The pincers break off easily. If it loses a pincer, it somehow becomes incapable of walking sideways.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: KRABBY live in holes dug into beaches. On sandy shores with little in the way of food, they can be seen squabbling with each other over territory.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.

Name: Krabby
FlavorText: If it is unable to find food, it will absorb nutrients by swallowing a mouthful of sand.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: The bubbles it spews out are strongly alkaline. Any opponents hit by them will have their bodies quickly melted away.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: The flow of Gigantamax energy has spurred this Pokémon’s left pincer to grow to an enormous size. That claw can pulverize anything.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: The larger pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: Its oversized claw is very powerful, but when it’s not in battle, the claw just gets in the way.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: One claw grew massively and is as hard as steel. It has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is too heavy.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: Kingler has an enormous, oversized claw. It waves this huge claw in the air to communicate with others. However, because the claw is so heavy, the Pokémon quickly tires.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: Its pincers grow peculiarly large. If it lifts the pincers too fast, it loses its balance and staggers.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: It can hardly lift its massive, overgrown pincer. The pincer’s size makes it difficult to aim properly.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: It waves its huge, oversized claw in the air to communicate with others. But since the claw is so heavy, this POKéMON quickly tires.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: The large pincer has 10,000-horsepower crushing force. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: One claw grew massively and as hard as steel. It has 10,000-HP strength. However, it is too heavy.

Name: Kingler
FlavorText: The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.

Name: Voltorb
FlavorText: An enigmatic Pokémon that happens to bear a resemblance to a Poké Ball. When excited, it discharges the electric current it has stored in its belly, then lets out a great, uproarious laugh.

Name: Electrode
FlavorText: The tissue on the surface of its body is curiously similar in composition to an Apricorn. When irritated, this Pokémon lets loose an electric current equal to 20 lightning bolts.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: These Pokémon get nervous when they’re not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing, Exeggcute become cowardly.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Though it may look like it’s just a bunch of eggs, it’s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: The heads attract each other and spin around. There must be six heads for it to maintain balance.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Although they are the same size as other Exeggcute, the ones produced in Alola are quite heavy. Their shells are packed full.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Six of them form a single Pokémon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Six of them together form a full-fledged Pokémon. It’s often hunted by Crabrawler, but uses psychokinesis to drive it off.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Its six eggs use telepathy to communicate among themselves. It is believed to carry plant genes and the genes of other species.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: This Pokémon consists of six eggs that form a closely knit cluster. The six eggs attract each other and spin around. When cracks increasingly appear on the eggs, Exeggcute is close to evolution.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Even though it appears to be eggs of some sort, it was discovered to be a life-form more like plant seeds.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Using telepathy only they can employ, they always form a cluster of six EXEGGCUTE.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Their shells are very durable. Even if they crack, they can survive without spilling their contents.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: It consists of six eggs that care for each other. The eggs attract each other and spin around. When cracks increasingly appear, it is close to evolution.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: It is often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: If even one is separated from the group, the energy bond between the six will make them rejoin instantly.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Using telepathy only they can receive, they always form a cluster of six EXEGGCUTE.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: The shell is very durable. Even if it cracks, it can survive without spilling the contents.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: The heads attract each other and spin around. There must be 6 heads for it to maintain balance.

Name: Exeggcute
FlavorText: Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s psychic powers aren’t as strong as they once were. The head on this Exeggutor’s tail scans surrounding areas with weak telepathy.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Blazing sunlight has brought out the true form and powers of this Pokémon.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: The strong sunlight of the Alola region has awakened the power hidden within Exeggcute. This is the result.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: It swings its long neck like a whip and smacks its opponents. This makes Exeggutor itself dizzy, too.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Exeggutor is the pride of the Alolan people. Its image is carved into historical buildings and murals.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers, while within it awakened the power of the sleeping dragon.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Alola is the best environment for this Pokémon. Local people take pride in its appearance, saying this is how Exeggutor ought to look.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: It is called the Walking Jungle. If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: When they work together, Exeggutor’s three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokémon sluggish.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Each of Exeggutor’s three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don’t seem to be very interested in one another.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Its cries are very noisy. This is because each of the three heads thinks about whatever it likes.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Each of its three heads has its own thoughts. When they want to go in different directions, Exeggutor becomes unable to move.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: It engages its enemies using psychic powers. Each of its three heads fires off psychokinetic energy, tripling its power.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: When the time comes, one of its three heads falls off. Before long, the fallen head grows into an Exeggcute.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Each of its heads has its own will. They use telepathy to discuss their plans before coming to a joint decision.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Exeggutor originally came from the tropics. Its heads steadily grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall off, they group together to form Exeggcute.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: It is called “The Walking Jungle.” If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Its three heads think independently. However, they are friendly and never appear to squabble.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: If a head drops off, it emits a telepathic call in search of others to form an EXEGGCUTE cluster.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Originally from the tropics, EXEGGUTOR’s heads grow larger from exposure to strong sunlight. It is said that when the heads fall, they group to form an EXEGGCUTE.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: It is said that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: It is called “The Walking Tropical Rainforest.” Each of the nuts has a face and a will of its own.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Living in a good environment makes it grow lots of heads. A head that drops off becomes an EXEGGCUTE.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Its cries are very noisy. This is because each of the 3 heads thinks about whatever it likes.

Name: Exeggutor
FlavorText: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: The cursed flames that light up the bone carried by this Pokémon are said to cause both mental and physical pain that will never fade.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: This Pokémon sets the bone it holds on fire and dances through the night as a way to mourn its fallen allies.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: It has transformed the spirit of its dear departed mother into flames, and tonight it will once again dance in mourning of others of its kind.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: When it beats opponents with its bone, the cursed flames spread to them. No amount of water will stop those flames from burning.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: The rich greenery of the Alola region is hard on Marowak. It controls fire to stay alive.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: Its custom is to mourn its lost companions. Mounds of dirt by the side of the road mark the graves of the Marowak.

Name: Marowak
FlavorText: The bones it possesses were once its mother’s. Its mother’s regrets have become like a vengeful spirit protecting this Pokémon.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: It is cloaked entirely in blue vines, preventing any glimpse of its true identity. The vines impart a refreshing sensation when chewed—they’re useful as a spice.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: It is shrouded by blue vines. No one has seen the face hidden behind this growth of vines.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: The vines of a Tangela have a distinct scent. In some parts of Galar, Tangela vines are used as herbs.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon’s true appearance remains a mystery.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Its identity is obscured by masses of thick blue vines. The vines are said to never stop growing.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Tangela’s vines snap off easily if they are grabbed. This happens without pain, allowing it to make a quick getaway. The lost vines are replaced by newly grown vines the very next day.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: It tangles any moving thing with its vines. Their subtle shaking is ticklish if you get ensnared.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: The blue vines shrouding its body are covered in a growth of fine hair. It is known to be ticklish.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: The vines that cloak its entire body are always jiggling. They effectively unnerve its foes.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Its vines snap off easily and painlessly if they are grabbed, allowing it to make a quick getaway. The lost vines are replaced by new growth the very next day.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to seaweed. The vines sway as it walks.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Blue plant vines cloak the POKéMON’s identity in a tangled mass. It entangles anything that gets close.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: During battle, it constantly moves the vines that cover its body in order to annoy its opponent.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: Its identity is obscured by masses of thick, blue vines. The vines are said to never stop growing.

Name: Tangela
FlavorText: The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to seaweed. Its vines shake as it walks.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits black ink and flees.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle currents. If this Pokémon is under attack, it spits out pitch-black ink and escapes.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: If it senses any danger, it will vigorously spray water or a special type of ink from its mouth.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: If Horsea senses danger, it will reflexively spray a dense black ink from its mouth and try to escape. This Pokémon swims by cleverly flapping the fin on its back.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: Horsea eats small insects and moss off of rocks. If the ocean current turns fast, this Pokémon anchors itself by wrapping its tail around rocks or coral to prevent being washed away.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: Its big, developed fins move rapidly, allowing it to swim backward while still facing forward.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: If attacked by a larger enemy, it quickly swims to safety by adeptly controlling its well-developed dorsal fin.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: By cleverly flicking the fins on its back side to side, it moves in any direction while facing forward. It spits ink to escape if it senses danger.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: It maintains balance using its tail, which is wound up like a coil. It may spray ink from its mouth.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: If HORSEA senses danger, it will reflexively spray a dense black ink from its mouth and try to escape. This POKéMON swims by cleverly flapping the fins on its back.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: When they’re in a safe location, they can be seen playfully tangling their tails together.

Name: Horsea
FlavorText: If attacked by a larger enemy, it quickly swims to safety by adeptly controlling its dorsal fin.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional medicine ingredients.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Seadra’s mouth is slender, but its suction power is strong. In an instant, Seadra can suck in food that’s larger than the opening of its mouth.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: It’s the males that raise the offspring. While Seadra are raising young, the spines on their backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Touching the back fin causes numbness. It hooks its tail to coral to stay in place while sleeping.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Seadra generates whirlpools by spinning its body. The whirlpools are strong enough to swallow even fishing boats. This Pokémon weakens prey with these currents, then swallows it whole.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Seadra sleeps after wriggling itself between the branches of coral. Those trying to harvest coral are occasionally stung by this Pokémon’s poison barbs if they fail to notice it.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: It is capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its winglike pectoral fins and stout tail.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Its body bristles with sharp spikes. Carelessly trying to touch it could cause fainting from the spikes.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional-medicine ingredients.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Its fin-tips leak poison. Its fins and bones are highly valued as ingredients in herbal medicine.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: An examination of its cells revealed the presence of a gene not found in HORSEA. It became a hot topic.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: The poisonous barbs all over its body are highly valued as ingredients for making traditional herbal medicine. It shows no mercy to anything approaching its nest.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: The male raises the young. If it is approached, it uses its toxic spikes to fend off the intruder.

Name: Seadra
FlavorText: Capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: It swims at a steady five knots. If it senses danger, it will strike back with its sharp horn.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: It swims elegantly by flittering its tail fin as if it were a dress. It has the look of a queen.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Its dorsal and pectoral fins are strongly developed like muscles. It can swim at a speed of five knots.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: When it is time for them to lay eggs, they can be seen swimming up rivers and falls in large groups.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: The way it swims along fluttering its dress-like fins has earned it the name “princess of the water.”

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Although known for their splendid tail fins, Goldeen apparently compete among themselves to see whose horn is thickest and sharpest.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Spellbound by the length of its horn and the beauty of its fins, many strange Trainers raise Goldeen and nothing but Goldeen.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: When the weather grows warm, they form groups and swim upriver. This sight serves as a poetic reminder that spring has arrived.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Goldeen loves swimming wild and free in rivers and ponds. If one of these Pokémon is placed in an aquarium, it will shatter even the thickest glass with one ram of its horn and make its escape.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Goldeen is a very beautiful Pokémon with fins that billow elegantly in water. However, don’t let your guard down around this Pokémon—it could ram you powerfully with its horn.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: It swims at a steady 5 knots. If it senses danger, it will strike back with its sharp horn.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Though it appears very elegant when swimming with fins unfurled, it can jab powerfully with its horn.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: A strong swimmer, it is capable of swimming nonstop up fast streams at a steady speed of five knots per hour.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Its dorsal, pectoral and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the water dancer.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: In the springtime, schools of GOLDEEN can be seen swimming up falls and rivers. It metes out staggering damage with its single horn.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of “The Water Queen.”

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: GOLDEEN is a very beautiful POKéMON with fins that billow elegantly in water. However, don’t let your guard down around this POKéMON - it could ram you powerfully with its horn.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: During spawning season, they swim gracefully in the water, searching for their perfect mate.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: A strong swimmer, it is capable of swimming nonstop up fast streams at a steady speed of five knots.

Name: Goldeen
FlavorText: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the Water Queen.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: To protect its family, it will fight with its drill-sharp horn. It lives in hollowed rocks in streams.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: It makes its nest by hollowing out boulders in streams with its horn. The Pokémon defends its eggs with its life.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: Using its horn, it bores holes in riverbed boulders, making nests to prevent its eggs from washing away.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: It is the male’s job to make a nest by carving out boulders in a stream using the horn on its head.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: To attract females, males dance on the river’s floor. The females gather around the male that dances most gracefully.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: Its horn spins like a drill to steadily hollow out rocks—even harder ones. The coloration of the male is more vivid.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: Trainers who are crazy for Seaking are divided into horn enthusiasts and fin enthusiasts. The two groups do not get along well.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: When the weather grows cold, its whole body flushes a deep red. This sight serves as a poetic reminder that autumn has arrived.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: Seaking is very protective of its eggs. The male and female will take turns patrolling around their nest and eggs. The guarding of eggs by these Pokémon goes on for over a month.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: In the autumn, Seaking males can be seen performing courtship dances in riverbeds to woo females. During this season, this Pokémon’s body coloration is at its most beautiful.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: It makes its nest by hollowing out boulders in streams with its horn. It defends its eggs with its life.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: During spawning season, SEAKING gather from all over, causing rivers to appear a brilliant red.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: It punches holes in boulders on streambeds. This is a clever innovation that prevents its eggs from being attacked or washed away by the current.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: The horn on its head is sharp like a drill. It bores a hole in a boulder to make its nest.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: When autumn comes, the males patrol the area around their nests in order to protect their offspring.

Name: Seaking
FlavorText: During spawning season, SEAKING gather from all over, coloring the rivers a brilliant red.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: If Staryu’s body is damaged, it will regenerate as long as the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: Fish Pokémon nibble at it, but Staryu isn’t bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you’ll be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a steady rhythm.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: As long as the center section is unharmed, this Pokémon can grow back fully even if it is chopped to bits.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: No number of injuries can bother Staryu. Its amazing regenerative powers return it to its previous state in half a day!

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: In many places, there are folktales of stardust falling into the ocean and becoming Staryu.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: This Pokémon gets nibbled on by Lumineon and others. Thanks to its red core, it regenerates fast, so it’s unconcerned by their snack attacks.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: Large numbers of these Pokémon make their home at the seaside. At night, a strange red glow radiates from the center of their bodies.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: Staryu apparently communicates with the stars in the night sky by flashing the red core at the center of its body. If parts of its body are torn, this Pokémon simply regenerates the missing pieces and limbs.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: Staryu’s center section has an organ called the core that shines bright red. If you go to a beach toward the end of summer, the glowing cores of these Pokémon look like the stars in the sky.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: Even if its body is torn, it can regenerate as long as the glowing central core remains intact.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: As long as its red core remains, it can regenerate its body instantly, even if it’s torn apart.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: If its body is torn, it can grow back if the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: At night, the middle of its body slowly flickers with the same rhythm as a human heartbeat.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: It gathers with others in the night and makes its red core glow on and off with the twinkling stars. It can regenerate limbs if they are severed from its body.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: An enigmatic POKéMON that can effortlessly regenerate any appendage it loses in battle.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: When the stars twinkle at night, it floats up from the sea floor, and its body’s center core flickers.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: At night, the center of its body slowly flickers with the same rhythm as a human heartbeat.

Name: Staryu
FlavorText: As long as the center section is unharmed, it can grow back fully even if it is chopped to bits.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: At the center of its body is a red core that sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokémon cruises through the ocean, it absorbs tiny plankton.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: This Pokémon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: The center section is named the core. People think it is communicating when it glows in seven colors.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: It rotates its geometrically shaped body to swim through the water. It always seems to be sending out mysterious radio waves.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Its sparkling core is called “the gem of the sea.” This core can be made into high-priced accessories that are traded in secret.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Its unusual body shape, reminiscent of abstract art, led local people to spread rumors that this Pokémon may be an invader from outer space.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Its shining core is thought to receive and transmit enigmatic signals. It has been known to cause headaches in those who approach it.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Starmie swims through water by spinning its star-shaped body as if it were a propeller on a ship. The core at the center of this Pokémon’s body glows in seven colors.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Starmie’s center section—the core—glows brightly in seven colors. Because of its luminous nature, this Pokémon has been given the nickname “the gem of the sea.”

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: At the center of its body is a red core, which sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Its core shines in many colors and sends radio signals into space to communicate with something.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: Regardless of the environment it lives in, its body grows to form a symmetrical geometric shape.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: The middle section of its body is called the core. It glows in a different color each time it is seen.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: People in ancient times imagined that STARMIE were transformed from the reflections of stars that twinkled on gentle waves at night.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: This POKéMON has a geometric body. Because of its body, the locals suspect that it is an alien creature.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: STARMIE’s center section - the core - glows brightly in seven colors. Because of its luminous nature, this POKéMON has been given the nickname “the gem of the sea.”

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: It is said that it uses the seven-colored core of its body to send electric waves into outer space.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: The center section of its body is called the core. It glows in a different color each time it is seen.

Name: Starmie
FlavorText: The center section is named the core. People think it is communicating when it glows in 7 colors.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Legend has it that this Pokémon was born from the crater of a volcano. When wounded, it bathes in lava to heal its body, much as one would soak in a hot spring.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: It was born in the crater of a volcano. Its body is covered with flames that shimmer like the sun.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: These Pokémon’s bodies are constantly burning. Magmar are feared as one of the causes behind fires.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Born in an active volcano. Its body is always cloaked in flames, so it looks like a big ball of fire.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: The hotter the place, the better they feel. Magmar in Alola are said to be hardier than those in other areas.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Its entire body is burning. When it breathes, the temperature rises. When it sneezes, flames shoot out!

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: When angered, it spouts brilliant fire from all over its body. It doesn’t calm down until its opponent has burned to ash.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: When it’s tired, it leaps into the mouth of a volcano and soaks its body in magma to ease its weariness. Its body burns at 2,192 degrees F.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: In battle, Magmar blows out intensely hot flames from all over its body to intimidate its opponent. This Pokémon’s fiery bursts create heat waves that ignite grass and trees in its surroundings.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Born in the spout of a volcano, its body is covered by flames that shimmer like the sun.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather’s body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: The scorching fire exhaled by Magmar forms heat waves around its body, making it hard to see the Pokémon clearly.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: When it breathes deeply, heat waves form around its body, making it hard to see clearly.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: The fiery surface of its body gives off a wavering, rippling glare that is similar to the sun.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: It dislikes cold places, so it blows scorching flames to make the environment suitable for itself.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: In battle, it blows out intense flames from all over its body to intimidate its foe. These fiery bursts create heat waves that ignite grass and trees in the area.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly amidst flames.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: It moves more frequently in hot areas. It can heal itself by dipping its wound into lava.

Name: Magmar
FlavorText: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: It swims by jetting water from its horns. The most notable characteristic of the Aqua Breed is its high body fat, which allows it to float easily.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: This Pokémon blasts water from holes on the tips of its horns—the high-pressure jets pierce right through Tauros’s enemies.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: People call this kind of Tauros the Blaze Breed due to the hot air it snorts from its nostrils. Its three tails are intertwined.

Name: Tauros
FlavorText: When heated by fire energy, its horns can get hotter than 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. Those gored by them will suffer both wounds and burns.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: A feeble, pitiful imbecile of a Pokémon that is nonetheless very hardy. Unperturbed by turbid water, it can be found living in all sorts of places.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: It is unable to swim against even slow-moving currents. It always splashes about for some reason.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: It is said to be the world’s weakest Pokémon. No one knows why it has managed to survive.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: This weak and pathetic Pokémon gets easily pushed along rivers when there are strong currents.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: It is virtually worthless in terms of both power and speed. It is the most weak and pathetic Pokémon in the world.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: Famous for being very unreliable. It can be found swimming in seas, lakes, rivers and shallow puddles.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: Thanks to their strong hold on life, dirty water doesn’t bother them at all. They live in waters all over the world!

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: In the distant past, they were fairly strong, but they have become gradually weaker over time.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: Its reckless leaps make it easy pickings for predators. On the bright side, many Pokémon enjoy longer life spans, thanks to Magikarp.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: Although weak and helpless, this Pokémon is incredibly fertile. They exist in such multitudes, you’ll soon grow tired of seeing them.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: Magikarp is virtually useless in battle as it can only splash around. As a result, it is considered to be weak. However, it is actually a very hardy Pokémon that can survive in any body of water no matter how polluted it is.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: Magikarp is a pathetic excuse for a Pokémon that is only capable of flopping and splashing. This behavior prompted scientists to undertake research into it.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: A Magikarp living for many years can leap a mountain using Splash. The move remains useless, though.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: For no reason, it jumps and splashes about, making it easy for predators like PIDGEOTTO to catch it mid-jump.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions, but usually not more than seven feet.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: Its swimming muscles are weak, so it is easily washed away by currents. In places where water pools, you can see many MAGIKARP deposited there by the flow.

Name: Magikarp
FlavorText: An underpowered, pathetic POKéMON. It may jump high on rare occasions, but never more than seven feet.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: Although it obeys its instinctive drive to destroy everything within its reach, it will respond to orders from a Trainer it truly trusts.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: It zooms out of the water at Mach speeds. Even large ships caught in its path are split cleanly in two!

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: Mega Evolution places a burden on its body. The stress causes it to become all the more ferocious.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: It jets water from the orifices on its sides, streaking above the water surface at supersonic speed.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: Mega Evolution also affects its brain, leaving no other function except its destructive instinct to burn everything to cinders.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: It appears whenever there is world conflict, burning down any place it travels through.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: I suspect this Pokémon to be the true identity of a dragon written of in ancient texts, which claimed that it razed an entire village with white-hot beams from its maw.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: In ancient literature, there is a record of a Gyarados that razed a village when violence flared.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: Once Gyarados appears, its rage never settles until the Pokémon has razed the fields and mountains around it.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: It has an extremely aggressive nature. The Hyper Beam it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: Brutally vicious and enormously destructive. Known for totally destroying cities in ancient times.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: The energy from evolution stimulated its brain cells strongly, causing it to become very ferocious.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: It fires hyper beams in all directions, burning the surrounding area to ash. There are some regions where it’s called “the deity of destruction.”

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: There are people who swear that any place Gyarados appears is fated for destruction.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: A tale is told of a town that angered Gyarados. Before the sun rose the next day, flames utterly consumed the town, leaving not a trace behind.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: Once Gyarados goes on a rampage, its ferociously violent blood doesn’t calm until it has burned everything down. There are records of this Pokémon’s rampages lasting a whole month.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: When Magikarp evolves into Gyarados, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this Pokémon’s wildly violent nature.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

Name: Gyarados
FlavorText: They say that during past strife, GYARADOS would appear and leave blazing ruins in its wake.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: It is hard for it to support its weight out of water, so it sometimes gets down on all fours. But it moves fast.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: It opens its huge mouth to intimidate enemies. In battle, it runs using its thick and powerful hind legs to charge the foe with incredible speed.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears up its victim.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: It is hard for it to support its own weight out of water, so it gets down on all fours. But it moves fast.

Name: Feraligatr
FlavorText: Although it has a massive body, its powerful hind legs enable it to move quickly, even on the ground.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: It discharges positive and negative electricity from the tips of its antennae to shock its foes.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: On the dark ocean floor, its only means of communication is its constantly flashing lights.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: Its antennae, which evolved from a fin, have both positive and negative charges flowing through them.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: Chinchou blink their shining antennae at one another to claim their respective turf.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: Its two antennae glow softly to lure in prey, making it a useful Pokémon for night fishing.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: It lives in the depths beyond the reach of sunlight. It flashes lights on its antennae to communicate with others of its kind.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: Its two antennae were originally fins. It discharges electricity to stun its prey before attacking.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: Chinchou’s two antennas are filled with cells that generate strong electricity. This Pokémon’s cells create so much electrical power, it even makes itself tingle slightly.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: Chinchou lets loose positive and negative electrical charges from its two antennas to make its prey faint. This Pokémon flashes its electric lights to exchange signals with others.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: It shoots positive and negative electricity between the tips of its two antennae and zaps its enemies.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: It discharges positive and negative electricity from its antenna tips to shock its foes.

Name: Chinchou
FlavorText: When it senses danger, it discharges positive and negative electricity from its two antennae. It lives in depths beyond sunlight’s reach.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: Lanturn’s light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed the Deep-Sea Star.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: The light it emits is so bright that it can illuminate the sea’s surface from a depth of over three miles.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: It lives far down in the depths of the ocean. It blinds its prey with light, using the moment they’re dazzled to swallow them whole.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: When the bacteria living inside its antennae absorb Lanturn’s bodily fluids, a strong luminescent effect is produced.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: Should you peer into the ocean at night and see a light shining like the stars, that is Lanturn.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: Lanturn is known to emit light. If you peer down into the dark sea from a ship at night, you can sometimes see this Pokémon’s light rising from the depths where it swims. It gives the sea an appearance of a starlit night.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: Lanturn is nicknamed “the deep-sea star” for its illuminated antenna. This Pokémon produces light by causing a chemical reaction between bacteria and its bodily fluids inside the antenna.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light. With the prey incapacitated, the Pokémon swallows it in a single gulp.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: Lanturn’s light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed “The Deep-Sea Star.”

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: The light-emitting orbs on its back are very bright. They are formed from a part of its dorsal fin. This POKéMON illuminates the inky darkness of deep seas.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light, then swallows the immobilized prey in a single gulp.

Name: Lanturn
FlavorText: This POKéMON uses the bright part of its body, which changed from a dorsal fin, to lure prey.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: Bellossom gather at times and appear to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: A Bellossom grows flowers more beautifully if it has evolved from a smelly Gloom—the more stinky the better. At night, this Pokémon closes its petals and goes to sleep.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: When Bellossom gets exposed to plenty of sunlight, the leaves ringing its body begin to spin around. This Pokémon’s dancing is renowned in the southern lands.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: Bellossom gather at times and seem to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: Its flower petals deepen in color through exposure to sunlight. When cloudy weather persists, it does a dance that is thought to be a ritual for summoning the sun.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: A BELLOSSOM grows flowers more beautifully if it has evolved from a smelly GLOOM - the stinkier the better. At night, this POKéMON closes its petals and goes to sleep.

Name: Bellossom
FlavorText: When these dance together, their petals rub against each other, making pretty, relaxing sounds.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The oil-filled tail functions as a buoy, so it’s fine even in rivers with strong currents.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry even when it plays in the water.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The tip of its tail is filled with oil that is lighter than water, so it acts as a float.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: Using its tail as a float, it dives underwater. It likes eating plants that grow in riverbeds.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: Even after Marill swims in a cold sea, its water- repellent fur dries almost as soon as Marill leaves the water. That’s why this Pokémon is never cold.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: This Pokémon uses its round tail as a float. The ball of Marill’s tail is filled with nutrients that have been turned into an oil.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: When fishing for food at the edge of a fast-running stream, Marill wraps its tail around the trunk of a tree. This Pokémon’s tail is flexible and configured to stretch.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: Marill’s oil-filled tail acts much like a life preserver. If you see just its tail bobbing on the water’s surface, it’s a sure indication that this Pokémon is diving beneath the water to feed on aquatic plants.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry, even when it plays in the water.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The oil-filled end of its tail floats on water. It keeps Marill from drowning even in a strong current.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The end of its tail serves as a buoy that keeps it from drowning, even in a vicious current.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: The tip of its tail, which contains oil that is lighter than water, lets it swim without drowning.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: Using its tail as a float, it dives underwater. It likes eating plants that grow on river bottoms.

Name: Marill
FlavorText: Its body is covered with water-repellent fur. Because of the fur, it can swim through water at high speed without being slowed by the water’s resistance.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: By keeping still and listening intently, it can tell what is in even wild, fast-moving rivers.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of living things on riverbeds.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: It lives in rivers and lakes. In water, its coloring and patterns trick the vision of foes.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: These Pokémon create air-filled bubbles. When Azurill play in rivers, Azumarill will cover them with these bubbles.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: It spends most of its time in the water. On sunny days, Azumarill floats on the surface of the water and sunbathes.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: Azumarill can make balloons out of air. It makes these air balloons if it spots a drowning Pokémon. The air balloons enable the Pokémon in trouble to breathe.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: Azumarill’s long ears are indispensable sensors. By focusing its hearing, this Pokémon can identify what kinds of prey are around, even in rough and fast-running rivers.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: The bubble-like pattern on its stomach helps it camouflage itself when it’s in the water.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: It can spend all day in water, since it can inhale and store a large volume of air.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: When it plays in water, it rolls up its elongated ears to prevent their insides from getting wet.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: It lives in water virtually all day long. Its body color and pattern act as camouflage that makes it tough for enemies to spot in water.

Name: Azumarill
FlavorText: By keeping still and listening intently, it can even tell what is in wild, fast-moving rivers.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: A group of Poliwag and Poliwhirl will form with a Politoed as the leader. Politoed’s cries make the Pokémon of the group obey.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: The cry of a male is louder than that of a female. Male Politoed with deep, menacing voices find more popularity with the opposite gender.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: At nightfall, these Pokémon appear on the shores of lakes. They announce their territorial claims by letting out cries that sound like shouting.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: The longer and more luxurious the curled hair on its head, the greater the number of Poliwag and Poliwhirl that will obey it.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: Although its cries sound like screams, a composer created a beautiful ballad that was influenced by the sounds.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: It’s the leader of Poliwag and Poliwhirl. When Politoed roars, they all cower in fear.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: They gather on moonlit nights to form a large chorus. Their cries sound angry and not at all pleasant, but they are certainly distinctive.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: The curled hair on Politoed’s head is proof of its status as a king. It is said that the longer and more curled the hair, the more respect this Pokémon earns from its peers.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: If Poliwag and Poliwhirl hear its echoing cry, they respond by gathering from far and wide.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: Whenever three or more of these get together, they sing in a loud voice that sounds like bellowing.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: It gathers groups of others as their leader. Its cries make Poliwag obey.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: The curled hair on its head proves its status as a king. It is said that the longer and curlier the hair, the more respect it earns from its peers.

Name: Politoed
FlavorText: When it expands its throat to croak out a tune, nearby POLIWAG and POLIWHIRL gather immediately.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: Outside of cold regions, Hoppip can be found practically everywhere. This is because the wind carries this species all over the world.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: This Pokémon is blown across vast distances by the wind. It is unclear where the Hoppip of Paldea originally came from.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: They are blown adrift by winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: This Pokémon drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, Hoppip links its leaves with other Hoppip to prepare against being blown away.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: Its body is so light, it must grip the ground firmly with its feet to keep from being blown away.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: To keep from being blown away by the wind, they gather in clusters. But they do enjoy gentle breezes.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: This POKéMON drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, a HOPPIP links leaves with others to prepare against being blown away.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: To keep from being blown away by the wind, they gather in clusters. They do enjoy gentle breezes, though.

Name: Hoppip
FlavorText: It can be carried away on even the gentlest breeze. It may even float all the way to the next town.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: When the weather grows cold, Skiploom’s flower closes and the Pokémon cannot photosynthesize, so it flies away to warmer regions.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: Skiploom enthusiasts can apparently tell where a Skiploom was born by the scent drifting from the flower on the Pokémon’s head.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: It blooms when the weather warms. It floats in the sky to soak up as much sunlight as possible.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: Skiploom’s flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees Fahrenheit. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this Pokémon is sometimes used as a thermometer.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: It spreads its petals to absorb sunlight. It also floats in the air to get closer to the sun.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: The bloom on top of its head opens and closes as the temperature fluctuates up and down.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: It blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees F. Because its flower’s blooming changes with the temperature, it is sometimes used as a thermometer.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: SKIPLOOM’s flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees F. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this POKéMON is sometimes used as a thermometer.

Name: Skiploom
FlavorText: As soon as it rains, it closes its flower and hides in the shade of a tree to avoid getting wet.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Beware its cotton spores. If you accidentally breathe them in, you’ll be racked with coughs and itchiness.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Jumpluff travels on seasonal winds. Once its cotton spores run out, its journey ends, as does its life.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Blown by seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Jumpluff rides warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. The Pokémon descends to the ground when it encounters cold air while it is floating.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Even in the fiercest wind, it can control its fluff to make its way to any place in the world it wants.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Drifts on seasonal winds and spreads its cotton-like spores all over the world to make more offspring.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Once it catches the wind, it deftly controls its cotton-puff spores--it can even float around the world.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: JUMPLUFF ride warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. This POKéMON lands when it encounters cold air while it is floating.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: Once it catches the wind, it deftly controls its cotton-puff spores to float, even around the world.

Name: Jumpluff
FlavorText: It drifts on seasonal winds and spreads its cotton-like spores all over the world  to make more offspring.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: It is very weak. Its only means of defense is to shake its leaves desperately at its attacker.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. Knowing it’s weak, it simply feeds until it evolves.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: They may suddenly fall out of the sky in the morning. In the year following a cold summer, their population explodes.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: Sunkern tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing, subsisting only on morning dew.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: It may plummet from the sky. If attacked by a Spearow, it will violently shake its leaves.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. A year after a cold summer, their population explodes.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: SUNKERN try to minimize movement to conserve the nutrients they have stored in their bodies for evolution. They will not eat, subsisting only on morning dew.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: It may drop out of the sky suddenly. If attacked by a SPEAROW, it will violently shake its leaves.

Name: Sunkern
FlavorText: SUNKERN tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing,  subsisting only on morning dew.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: Since it converts sunlight into energy, it is always looking in the direction of the sun.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: In the daytime, it rushes about in a hectic manner, but it comes to a complete stop when the sun sets.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: Sunflora converts solar energy into nutrition. It moves around actively in the daytime when it is warm. It stops moving as soon as the sun goes down for the night.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: As the hot season approaches, the petals on this Pokémon’s face become more vivid and lively.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: It converts sunlight into energy. In the darkness after sunset, it closes its petals and becomes still.

Name: Sunflora
FlavorText: SUNFLORA convert solar energy into nutrition. They are highly active in the warm daytime but suddenly stop moving as soon as the sun sets.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: When the temperature cools in the evening, they emerge from water to seek food along the shore.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: It lives in cold water, half burying itself in mud at the bottom to sleep.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: When walking on land, it covers its body with a poisonous film that keeps its skin from dehydrating.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: Wooper usually lives in water. However, it occasionally comes out onto land in search of food. On land, it coats its body with a gooey, toxic film.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: When it walks around on the ground, it coats its body with a slimy, poisonous film.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: WOOPER usually live in water but come out onto land seeking food occasionally. On land, they coat their bodies with a gooey, toxic film.

Name: Wooper
FlavorText: A mucous membrane covers its body. Touching it barehanded will cause a shooting pain.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: A dim-witted Pokémon. It doesn’t care if it bumps its head into boats or rocks while swimming.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: It has a sluggish nature. It lies at the river’s bottom, waiting for prey to stray into its mouth.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: Its body is always slimy. It often bangs its head on the river bottom as it swims but seems not to care.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: It has an easygoing nature. It doesn’t care if it bumps its head on boats and boulders while swimming.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: Quagsire hunts for food by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in unaware. Because the Pokémon does not move, it does not get very hungry.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: This carefree Pokémon has an easygoing nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: Due to its relaxed and carefree attitude, it often bumps its head on boulders and boat hulls as it swims.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: This carefree Pokémon has an easy-going nature. While swimming, it always bumps into boat hulls.

Name: Quagsire
FlavorText: A QUAGSIRE hunts by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in. Because it doesn’t move, it does not get very hungry.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: It has incredible intellect and intuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: When its head was bitten, toxins entered Slowpoke’s head and unlocked an extraordinary power.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: Being bitten by Shellder gave it intelligence comparable to that of internationally recognized scientists.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: Slowking can solve any problem presented to it, but no one can understand a thing Slowking says.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: Miraculously, this former Slowpoke’s latent intelligence was drawn out when Shellder poison raced through its brain.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: It’s called “the sage of the sea.” It engages in battles of wits with Oranguru, but the result is usually a draw.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: It’s constantly coming up with new ideas that would change the world, but as soon as it hits upon a new idea, it forgets it.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: This Pokémon is so famed for its intellect that a proverb still persists in some regions: “When in doubt, ask Slowking.”

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: A poisonous bite reacted with its system, blessing it with the enhanced intellect of a genius. It has full control of its psychic powers.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: Slowking undertakes research every day in an effort to solve the mysteries of the world. However, this Pokémon apparently forgets everything it has learned if the Shellder on its head comes off.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: Being bitten by Shellder gave it intelligence comparable to that of award-winning scientists.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: It undertakes research every day to solve the mysteries of the world. However, it apparently forgets everything if the SHELLDER on its head comes off.

Name: Slowking
FlavorText: Every time it yawns, SHELLDER injects more poison into it. The poison makes it more intelligent.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: Experienced fishers say they try to catch Qwilfish in the brief moment that these Pokémon become defenseless just after launching poisonous spikes.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: Be cautious if this Pokémon starts sucking in water—it will soon attack by scattering the toxic spikes that grow all over its body.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: It shoots the poison spikes on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: When faced with a larger opponent, it swallows as much water as it can to match the opponent’s size.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: Qwilfish sucks in water, inflating itself. This Pokémon uses the pressure of the water it swallowed to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming somewhat challenging.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: A QWILFISH uses the pressure of water it swallows to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming to be somewhat challenging.

Name: Qwilfish
FlavorText: To fire its poison spikes, it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of  water all at once.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn’t keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: Slugma does not have any blood in its body. Instead, intensely hot magma circulates throughout this Pokémon’s body, carrying essential nutrients and oxygen to its organs.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: Molten magma courses throughout Slugma’s circulatory system. If this Pokémon is chilled, the magma cools and hardens. Its body turns brittle and chunks fall off, reducing its size.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: A common sight in volcanic areas, it slowly slithers around in a constant search for warm places.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: It never sleeps. It has to keep moving because if it stopped, its magma body would cool and harden.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: It is a species of POKéMON that lives in volcanic areas. If its body cools, its skin hardens and immobilizes it. To avoid that, it sleeps near magma.

Name: Slugma
FlavorText: These group together in areas that are hotter than normal. If it cools off, its skin hardens.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit. Flames burst from gaps in its shell made of hardened magma.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Magcargo’s body temperature is approximately 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit. Water is vaporized on contact. If this Pokémon is caught in the rain, the raindrops instantly turn into steam, cloaking the area in a thick fog.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Magcargo’s shell is actually its skin that hardened as a result of cooling. Its shell is very brittle and fragile—just touching it causes it to crumble apart. This Pokémon returns to its original size by dipping itself in magma.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that circulate throughout its body.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees F. Flames spout from gaps in its hardened shell.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: Its brittle shell occasionally spouts intense flames that  circulate throughout its body.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: The shell on its back is just skin that has cooled and hardened. It breaks easily with a slight touch.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: The shell on its back is made of hardened magma. Tens of thousands of years spent living in volcanic craters have turned MAGCARGO’s bodies into magma.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: MAGCARGO’s body temperature is approximately 18,000 degrees F. Water is vaporized on contact. If this POKéMON is caught in the rain, the raindrops instantly turn into steam, cloaking the area in a thick fog.

Name: Magcargo
FlavorText: MAGCARGO’s shell is actually its skin that hardened as a result of cooling. Its shell is very brittle and fragile - just touching it causes it to crumble apart. This POKéMON returns to its original size by dipping itself in magma.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can’t live in polluted waters.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: These Pokémon live in warm seas. In prehistoric times, many lived in the oceans around the Galar region as well.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: It will regrow any branches that break off its head. People keep particularly beautiful Corsola branches as charms to promote safe childbirth.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: In Alola, where their natural enemies Mareanie are plentiful, many Corsola have stubby branches on their heads.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: The pink of Corsola that live in Alola is deep and vibrant, thanks to seas filled with nutrition.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: Pursued by Mareanie for the branches on its head, this Pokémon will sometimes snap its own branches off as a diversion while it escapes.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: Coral branches grow from its head. They break off quite easily, but they grow back in about three days.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: Clusters of Corsola congregate in warm seas where they serve as ideal hiding places for smaller Pokémon. When the water temperature falls, this Pokémon migrates to the southern seas.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: Corsola’s branches glitter very beautifully in seven colors when they catch sunlight. If any branch breaks off, this Pokémon grows it back in just one night.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: They prefer unpolluted southern seas. Their coral branches lose their color and deteriorate in dirty water.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure because of its beauty.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: In a south-sea nation, the people live in communities that are built on groups of these Pokémon.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: CORSOLA live in warm southern seas. If the sea becomes polluted, the beautiful coral stalks become discolored and crumble away in tatters.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure for its beauty.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: In a south sea nation, the people live in communities that are built on groups of these POKéMON.

Name: Corsola
FlavorText: The points on its head absorb nutrients from clean water. They cannot survive in polluted water.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: Spits water from its mouth with incredible accuracy. It captures Burmy by shooting them down off the branches from which they dangle.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: It clings to Mantine to feed on the big Pokémon’s scraps. This is an adaptation to avoid foes.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: It squirts water forcefully from its mouth to shoot down flying prey.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine’s underside to scavenge for leftovers.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: The water they shoot from their mouths can hit moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: Also known as the “sniper of the seas,” its water gun can hit prey without fail from over 300 feet away.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: This Pokémon clings to Mantine and shares in its prosperity. When its Mantine is attacked, Remoraid will fight alongside it!

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: Remoraid sucks in water, then expels it at high velocity using its abdominal muscles to shoot down flying prey. When evolution draws near, this Pokémon travels downstream from rivers.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: It has superb accuracy. The water it shoots out can strike moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: It forcefully squirts water. The water jet never misses prey even if the Remoraid is deep in the sea.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: A REMORAID uses its abdominal muscles to forcefully expel swallowed water, then shoot down flying prey. When evolution approaches, it travels down rivers.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: It has superb accuracy. The water it shoots out can strike even moving prey from more than 100 yards.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: To escape from an attacker, it may shoot water out of its mouth, then use that force to swim backward.

Name: Remoraid
FlavorText: It has superb accuracy. The water it shoots out can strike even moving prey from more than 300 feet.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: While Octillery still shoots water from its mouth, the drastic anatomical difference between it and Remoraid meant that for a long time, no one believed the former evolved from the latter.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It obscures its foe’s vision by spitting a cloud of black ink. It makes its nest among boulders.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It lives in the gaps of boulders and in holes on the seafloor. Its suction cups grip prey tightly.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It usually sleeps in caves. The pitch-black ink that Octillery spits is also used for cooking.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: The ink it spits when escaping is special. It contains a substance that dulls the sense of smell, so Pokémon with keen noses get lost.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: Octillery grabs onto its foe using its tentacles. This Pokémon tries to immobilize it before delivering the finishing blow. If the foe turns out to be too strong, Octillery spews ink to escape.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It traps foes with the suction cups on its tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It loves to lurk inside holes in rocks. It sometimes sprays ink on prey by sticking out only its mouth.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It instinctively sneaks into rocky holes. If it gets sleepy, it steals the nest of a fellow OCTILLERY.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It obscures its foe’s vision by spitting a cloud of murky ink. It makes its nest among boulders.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It ensnares its foe with its suction-cupped tentacles before delivering the finishing blow. If the foe turns out to be too strong, it spews ink to escape.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: Its instinct is to bury itself in holes. It often steals the nesting holes of others to sleep in them.

Name: Octillery
FlavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: This calm and gentle Pokémon swims gracefully through the sea. After building speed, it can leap out of the water. It is often misidentified as a bird Pokémon due to this behavior.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: It swims elegantly, mindless of Remoraid hitching onto its broad fins. It is naturally docile.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: When the waves are calm, one may encounter a swarm of Mantine swimming as if they are in flight.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: As it majestically swims, it doesn’t care if Remoraid attach to it to scavenge for its leftovers.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: Many people have taken up surfing because they admire how magnificently Mantine swims.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: Postcards and posters featuring Mantine leaping elegantly above the waves are popular souvenirs of Alola.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: On sunny days, schools of Mantine can be seen elegantly leaping over the sea’s waves. This Pokémon is not bothered by the Remoraid that hitches rides.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: While elegantly swimming in the sea, it ignores Remoraid that cling to its fins seeking food scraps.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can fly over 300 feet out of the water from the surface of the ocean.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: Swimming freely in open seas, it may fly out of the water and over the waves if it builds up enough speed.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: As it majestically swims, it doesn’t care if REMORAID attach to it for scavenging its leftovers.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: It swims elegantly, mindless of REMORAID hitching on to its broad fins. It has a docile nature.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: On sunny days, schools of MANTINE can be seen elegantly leaping over the waves. It is not bothered by the REMORAID that hitches rides.

Name: Mantine
FlavorText: It swims along freely, eating things that swim into its mouth. Its whole body is very coarse.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: It conveys its feelings using different cries. It works in a pack to cleverly take down prey.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: They make repeated eerie howls before dawn to call attention to their pack.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: It cooperates with others skillfully. When it becomes your partner, it’s very loyal to you as its Trainer and will obey your orders.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: Houndour hunt as a coordinated pack. They communicate with each other using a variety of cries to corner their prey. This Pokémon’s remarkable teamwork is unparalleled.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: To corner prey, they check each other’s location using barks that only they can understand.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: Around dawn, its ominous howl echoes through the area to announce that this is its territory.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: HOUNDOUR communicate with each other using a variety of cries to corner their prey. This POKéMON’s remarkable teamwork is simply unparalleled.

Name: Houndour
FlavorText: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing prey.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: Houndoom’s entire body generates heat when it Mega Evolves. Its fearsome fiery breath turns its opponents to ash.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: Its red claws and the tips of its tail are melting from high internal temperatures that are painful to Houndoom itself.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: Long ago, people imagined its eerie howls to be the call of the grim reaper.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: They spew flames mixed with poison to finish off their opponents. They divvy up their prey evenly among the members of their pack.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: In a Houndoom pack, the one with its horns raked sharply toward the back serves a leadership role. These Pokémon choose their leader by fighting among themselves.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: In a HOUNDOOM pack, the one with its horns raked sharply back serves a leadership role. They choose their leader by fighting among themselves.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: In a HOUNDOOM pack, the one with its horns raked sharply towards the back serves a leadership role. These POKéMON choose their leader by fighting amongst themselves.

Name: Houndoom
FlavorText: The pungent-smelling flame that shoots from its mouth results from toxins burning in its body.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: It lives in caves on the seafloor and creates giant whirlpools every time it moves.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: Scales shed by this Pokémon have such a splendorous gleam to them that they’ve been given to royalty as gifts.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: With the arrival of a storm at sea, this Pokémon will show itself on the surface. When a Kingdra and a Dragonite meet, a fierce battle ensues.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: Kingdra sleeps on the seafloor where it is otherwise devoid of life. When a storm arrives, the Pokémon is said to awaken and wander about in search of prey.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: Kingdra lives at extreme ocean depths that are otherwise uninhabited. It has long been believed that the yawning of this Pokémon creates spiraling ocean currents.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life-forms can survive.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: It sleeps deep on the ocean floor to build its energy. It is said to cause tornadoes as it wakes.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: It sleeps quietly, deep on the seafloor. When it comes up to the surface, it creates a huge whirlpool that can swallow even ships.

Name: Kingdra
FlavorText: It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life forms can survive.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives in volcanic areas. With each breath, sparks spurt from its mouth and nose. When Magby is in good health, its flames gain a yellow tint.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Its body temperature is around 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit. It is healthy if it is exhaling yellow flames.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: This Pokémon makes its home near volcanoes. At the end of the day, Magby soaks in magma, resting and recovering from the day’s fatigue.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: This Pokémon is still small and timid. Whenever Magby gets excited or surprised, flames leak from its mouth and its nose.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Its body temperature is always around 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit. If Magby falls into a small- enough pond, the whole thing will dry up.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: When flames drip from its nose, that means it has a cold. Have it lie down for a nice rest in some magma.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: A famous potter lives with a Magby. Apparently its soft flames produce fine works.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Many of these Pokémon can be seen in areas with volcanic activity. Feeding can get them so excited, they exhale flames of 1,100 degrees F.

Name: Magby
