FlavorText: Magby’s state of health is determined by observing the fire it breathes. If the Pokémon is spouting yellow flames from its mouth, it is in good health. When it is fatigued, black smoke will be mixed in with the flames.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Its magma-like blood circulates throughout its body. Its body’s heat can top 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: It’s small, but its body temperature is over 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit. Embers escape its mouth and nose when it breathes.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: It’s small, but its body temperature is over 1,100 degrees F. Embers escape its mouth and nose when it breathes.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Its magma-like blood circulates throughout its body. Its body’s heat can top 1,100 degrees F.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: It is found in volcanic craters. Its body temperature is over 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit, so don’t underestimate it.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Each and every time it inhales and exhales, hot embers dribble from its mouth and nostrils.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Its body temperature is around 1,100 degrees F. It is healthy if it is breathing yellow flames.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: If a MAGBY is spouting yellow flames from its mouth, it is in good health. When it is fatigued, black smoke will be mixed in with the flames.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: Each and every time it inhales and exhales, hot embers dribble out of its mouth and nostrils.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: It is found in volcanic craters. Its body heat exceeds 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit, so don’t underestimate it.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: It naturally spits an 1100-degree flame. It is said when many appear, it heralds a volcanic eruption.

Name: Magby
FlavorText: It is found in volcanic craters. Its body temp. is over 1100 degrees, so don’t underestimate it.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: A Pokémon that races across the land. It is said that one is born every time a new volcano appears.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: Volcanoes erupt when it barks. Unable to contain its sheer power, it races headlong around the land.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: ENTEI embodies the passion of magma. It is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It blasts fire that consumes all that it touches.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: Volcanoes erupt when it barks. Unable to restrain its extreme power, it races headlong around the land.

Name: Entei
FlavorText: This brawny POKéMON courses around the earth, spouting flames hotter than a volcano’s magma.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: This Pokémon races across the land. It is said that north winds will somehow blow whenever it appears.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: SUICUNE embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gliding elegance. It has the power to purify dirty water.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: Said to be the reincarnation of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.

Name: Suicune
FlavorText: This divine POKéMON blows around the world, always in search of a pure reservoir.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: Its feathers are in seven colors. It is said that anyone seeing it is promised eternal happiness.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: Ho-Oh’s feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: It will reveal itself before a pure-hearted Trainer by shining its bright, rainbow-colored wings.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind it when it flies.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: Legends claim this Pokémon flies the world’s skies continuously on its magnificent, seven-colored wings.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: Its feathers--which glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light--are thought to bring joy. It is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: Legends claim this POKéMON flies the world’s skies continuously on its magnificent seven-colored wings.

Name: Ho-oh
FlavorText: It will reveal itself before a pure-hearted trainer by shining its bright rainbow-colored wings.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: This Pokémon traveled through time to come from the future. It bolsters grass and trees with its own strength, and it can heal wounds, too.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: This Pokémon has the ability to move through time. Records describing it as a forest deity can be found from many different eras.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: When CELEBI disappears deep in a forest, it is said to leave behind an egg it brought from the future.

Name: Celebi
FlavorText: Revered as a guardian of the forest, CELEBI appears wherever beautiful forests exist.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny hooks, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: Treecko is cool, calm, and collected—it never panics under any situation. If a bigger foe were to glare at this Pokémon, it would glare right back without conceding an inch of ground.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: Treecko has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This Pokémon attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: It quickly scales even vertical walls. It senses humidity with its tail to predict the next day’s weather.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny spikes, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: It makes its nest in a giant tree in the forest. It ferociously guards against anything nearing its territory. It is said to be the protector of the forest’s trees.

Name: Treecko
FlavorText: TREECKO is cool, calm, and collected - it never panics under any situation. If a bigger foe were to glare at this POKéMON, it would glare right back without conceding an inch of ground.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: This Pokémon adeptly flies from branch to branch in trees. In a forest, no Pokémon can ever hope to catch a fleeing Grovyle however fast they may be.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: The leaves growing out of Grovyle’s body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This Pokémon is a master at climbing trees in jungles.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: Its strongly developed thigh muscles give it astounding agility and jumping performance.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: It lives in dense jungles. While  closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: It leaps from tree branch to tree branch quite swiftly. It shows astounding agility.

Name: Grovyle
FlavorText: Leaves grow out of this POKéMON’s body. They help obscure a GROVYLE from the eyes of its enemies while it is in a thickly overgrown forest.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: Sceptile has seeds growing on its back. They are said to be bursting with nutrients that revitalize trees. This Pokémon raises the trees in a forest with loving care.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: The leaves growing on Sceptile’s body are very sharp edged. This Pokémon is very agile—it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: It agilely leaps about the jungle and uses the sharp leaves on its arms to strike its prey.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: In the jungle, its power is without equal. This POKéMON carefully grows trees and plants. It regulates its body temperature by basking in sunlight.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: The leaves on its forelegs are as sharp as swords. It agilely leaps about the branches of trees to strike.

Name: Sceptile
FlavorText: The leaves growing on SCEPTILE’s body are very sharp edged. This POKéMON is very agile - it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: A fire burns inside it, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: Torchic has a place inside its body where it keeps its flame. Give it a hug—it will be glowing with warmth. This Pokémon is covered all over by a fluffy coat of down.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: Torchic sticks with its Trainer, following behind with unsteady steps. This Pokémon breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: It has a flame sac inside its belly that perpetually burns. It feels warm if it is hugged.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees F.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: Inside its body is a place where it keeps a small flame. Hug it! It will be as warm as a hot-water bottle.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: If attacked, it strikes back by spitting balls of fire it forms in its stomach. A TORCHIC dislikes darkness because it can’t see its surroundings.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: TORCHIC has a place inside its body where it keeps its flame. Give it a hug - it will be glowing with warmth. This POKéMON is covered all over by a fluffy coat of down.

Name: Torchic
FlavorText: TORCHIC sticks with its TRAINER, following behind with unsteady steps. This POKéMON breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees F, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: Combusken battles with the intensely hot flames it spews from its beak and with outstandingly destructive kicks. This Pokémon’s cry is very loud and distracting.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: Combusken toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This Pokémon’s legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out 10 kicks in one second.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: During a battle, the hot flame in its body increases. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: It lashes out with 10 kicks per second. Its strong fighting instinct compels it to keep up its offensive until the opponent gives up.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: It boosts its concentration by emitting harsh cries. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

Name: Combusken
FlavorText: COMBUSKEN toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This POKéMON’s legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out ten kicks in one second.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: Flames spout from its wrists, enveloping its knuckles. Its punches scorch its foes.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: Blaziken has incredibly strong legs—it can easily clear a 30-story building in one leap. This Pokémon’s blazing punches leave its foes scorched and blackened.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: In battle, Blaziken blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this Pokémon’s wrists burn.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: It can clear a 30-story building in a leap. Its fiery punches scorch its foes.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: It learns martial arts that use punches and kicks. Every several years, its old feathers burn off, and new, supple feathers grow back in their place.

Name: Blaziken
FlavorText: BLAZIKEN has incredibly strong legs - it can easily clear a 30-story building in one leap. This POKéMON’s blazing punches leave its foes scorched and blackened.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: Using the fin on its head, Mudkip senses the flow of water to keep track of what’s going on around it. Mudkip has the strength to heft boulders.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: In water, Mudkip breathes using the gills on its cheeks. If it is faced with a tight situation in battle, this Pokémon will unleash its amazing power—it can crush rocks bigger than itself.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: The fin on Mudkip’s head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this Pokémon can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: Its large tail fin propels it through water with powerful acceleration. It is strong in spite of its size.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: Its power can crush boulders. It rests by covering itself with mud at the bottom of a river.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: On land, it can powerfully lift large boulders by planting its four feet and heaving. It sleeps by burying itself in soil at the water’s edge.

Name: Mudkip
FlavorText: In water, MUDKIP breathes using the gills on its cheeks. If it is faced with a tight situation in battle, this POKéMON will unleash its amazing power - it can crush rocks bigger than itself.

Name: Marshtomp
FlavorText: Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.

Name: Marshtomp
FlavorText: Marshtomp is much faster at traveling through mud than it is at swimming. This Pokémon’s hindquarters exhibit obvious development, giving it the ability to walk on just its hind legs.

Name: Marshtomp
FlavorText: The surface of Marshtomp’s body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This Pokémon plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.

Name: Marshtomp
FlavorText: Living on muddy ground that provides poor footing has made its legs sturdy.

Name: Marshtomp
FlavorText: Its toughened hind legs enable it to stand upright. Because it weakens if its skin dries out, it replenishes fluids by playing in mud.

Name: Marshtomp
FlavorText: It is at its best when on muddy ground with poor footing. It quickly overwhelms foes struggling in mud.

Name: Swampert
FlavorText: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.

Name: Swampert
FlavorText: Swampert predicts storms by sensing subtle differences in the sounds of waves and tidal winds with its fins. If a storm is approaching, it piles up boulders to protect itself.

Name: Swampert
FlavorText: Swampert is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This Pokémon also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.

Name: Swampert
FlavorText: Its arms are hard as rock. With one swing, it can break a boulder into pieces.

Name: Swampert
FlavorText: If it senses the approach of a storm and a tidal wave, it protects its seaside nest by piling up boulders. It swims as fast as a jet ski.

Name: Swampert
FlavorText: Its arms are rock-hard. With one swing, they can batter down its foe. It makes its nest on beautiful beaches.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon that try to peck at it.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokémon.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: Seedot looks exactly like an acorn when it is dangling from a tree branch. It startles other Pokémon by suddenly moving. This Pokémon polishes its body once a day using leaves.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: Seedot attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch. The more water it drinks, the glossier this Pokémon’s body becomes.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: It hangs off branches and absorbs nutrients. When it finishes eating, its body becomes so heavy that it drops to the ground with a thump.

Name: Seedot
FlavorText: If it remains still, it becomes impossible to distinguish from real nuts. It delights in surprising foraging PIDGEY.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in the forest.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: They live in holes bored in large trees. The sound of Nuzleaf’s grass flute fills listeners with dread.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: This Pokémon pulls out the leaf on its head and makes a flute with it. The sound of Nuzleaf’s flute strikes fear and uncertainty in the hearts of people lost in a forest.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: Nuzleaf live in densely overgrown forests. They occasionally venture out of the forest to startle people. This Pokémon dislikes having its long nose pinched.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in forests.

Name: Nuzleaf
FlavorText: A forest-dwelling POKéMON that is skilled at climbing trees. Its long and pointed nose is its weak point. It loses power if the nose is gripped.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: By flapping its leafy fans, it can whip up gusts of 100 feet per second that can level houses.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: It lives quietly in the deep forest. It is said to create chilly winter winds with the fans it holds.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe’s mind and take preemptive action.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: Shiftry’s large fans generate awesome gusts of wind at a speed close to 100 feet per second. The whipped-up wind blows anything away. This Pokémon chooses to live quietly deep in forests.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: Shiftry is a mysterious Pokémon that is said to live atop towering trees dating back over a thousand years. It creates terrific windstorms with the fans it holds.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 feet per second that can level houses.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 ft/second that can level houses.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: It is said to arrive on chilly, wintry winds. Feared from long ago as the guardian of forests, this POKéMON lives in a deep forest where people do not venture.

Name: Shiftry
FlavorText: SHIFTRY is a mysterious POKéMON that is said to live atop towering trees  dating back over a thousand years. It creates terrific windstorms with the fans it holds.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It rides upon ocean winds as if it were a glider. In the winter, it hides food around its nest.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It soars high in the sky, riding on updrafts like a glider. It carries food tucked in its bill.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: Catching sea winds with its long wings, it soars as if it were a glider. It folds its wings to rest.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It makes its nest on steep sea cliffs. Riding updrafts, it soars to great heights.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It soars on updrafts without flapping its wings. It makes a nest on sheer cliffs at the sea’s edge.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It makes its nest on sheer cliffs. Riding the sea breeze, it glides up into the expansive skies.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It builds nests in cliffs by the sea. It circles the skies above the ocean looking for its favorite food—Wishiwashi.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: With its long, thin wings, it catches updrafts and flies like a glider high up into the sky.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: Fishermen keep an eye out for Wingull in the sky, because wherever they’re circling, the ocean is sure to be teeming with fish Pokémon.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: Its hollow bones enhance its lightness. It spreads its wings to the wind and soars away into the sky.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: Wingull rides updrafts rising from the sea by extending its long and narrow wings to glide. This Pokémon’s long beak is useful for catching prey.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: Wingull has the habit of carrying prey and valuables in its beak and hiding them in all sorts of locations. This Pokémon rides the winds and flies as if it were skating across the sky.

Name: Wingull
FlavorText: It makes its nest on a sheer cliff at the edge of the sea. It has trouble keeping its wings flapping in flight. Instead, it soars on updrafts.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It protects its young in its beak. It bobs on waves, resting on them on days when the waters are calm.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon in its beak. It bobs on the waves to rest its wings.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It acts as a delivery service by carrying small Pokémon in its bill. It bobs on the waves to rest.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It dips its large bill in the sea, then scoops up numerous prey along with water.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: Skimming the water’s surface, it dips its large bill in the sea, scoops up food and water, and carries it.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small Pokémon and eggs to safety in its bill.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It scoops up Wishiwashi in its huge beak and swallows them whole. It can devour more than 30 at one go!

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It places small Pokémon into its spacious beak and carries them around. No one knows where it’s taking them.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: Gathering food is the work of young males. They store food in their capacious beaks and carry it back to others waiting in the nest.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: Its spacious beak is large enough for a small child to fit right inside.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: Pelipper searches for food while in flight by skimming the wave tops. This Pokémon dips its large bill in the sea to scoop up food, then swallows everything in one big gulp.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: Pelipper is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon and eggs inside its massive bill. This Pokémon builds its nest on steep cliffs facing the sea.

Name: Pelipper
FlavorText: It skims the tops of waves as it flies. When it spots prey, it uses its large beak to scoop up the victim with water. It protects its eggs in its beak.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: It secretes a thick, sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: They usually live on ponds, but after an evening shower, they may appear on puddles in towns.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey in with a sweet scent released from the tip of its head.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: It lives in ponds and marshes that feature lots of plant life. It often fights with Dewpider, whose habitat and diet are similar.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: If it’s in a pinch, it will secrete a sweet liquid from the tip of its head. Syrup made from gathering that liquid is tasty on bread.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: When this Pokémon senses danger, a sweet fluid oozes from the tip of its head. The taste of it disgusts bird Pokémon.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: It moves as if skating on the surface of the water. It often fights with Dewpider over food.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: If Surskit senses danger, it secretes a thick, sugary syrup from the tip of its head. There are some Pokémon that love eating this syrup.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: From the tips of its feet, Surskit secretes an oil that enables it to walk on water as if it were skating. This Pokémon feeds on microscopic organisms in ponds and lakes.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.

Name: Surskit
FlavorText: They gather on puddles after evening downpours, gliding across the surface of water as if sliding. It secretes honey with a sweet aroma from its head.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: If it senses danger, it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over the body if inhaled.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: If Shroomish senses danger, it shakes its body and scatters spores from the top of its head. This Pokémon’s spores are so toxic, they make trees and weeds wilt.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: Shroomish live in damp soil in the dark depths of forests. They are often found keeping still under fallen leaves. This Pokémon feeds on compost that is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

Name: Shroomish
FlavorText: It loves to eat damp, composted soil in forests. If you enter a forest after a long rain, you can see many SHROOMISH feasting on composted soil.

Name: Breloom
FlavorText: The seeds on its tail are made of toxic spores. It knocks out foes with quick, virtually invisible punches.

Name: Breloom
FlavorText: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

Name: Breloom
FlavorText: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.

Name: Breloom
FlavorText: The seeds ringing Breloom’s tail are made of hardened toxic spores. It is horrible to eat the seeds. Just taking a bite of this Pokémon’s seed will cause your stomach to rumble.

Name: Breloom
FlavorText: Breloom closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. This Pokémon’s fighting technique puts boxers to shame.

Name: Breloom
FlavorText: It scatters spores from holes in the cap on its head. It loves warm and humid climates. It feeds on trees and plants in fields and forests.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: Though beautiful, it has highly poisonous thorns. There is an old tradition in my homeland wherein one would send these thorns to an opponent to challenge them to a duel.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: The beautiful flowers on its arms have toxic thorns. Don’t even think about picking those flowers.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: Roselia raised on clean drinking water are known to grow vividly colored flowers.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: It uses the different poisons in each hand separately when it attacks. The stronger its aroma, the healthier it is.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: On extremely rare occasions, a Roselia is said to appear with its flowers in unusual colors. The thorns on this Pokémon’s head contain a vicious poison.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: Roselia shoots sharp thorns as projectiles at any opponent that tries to steal the flowers on its arms. The aroma of this Pokémon brings serenity to living things.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: Roselia that drink nutritionally rich springwater are said to reveal rare coloration when they bloom.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: The more healthy the Roselia, the more pleasant its flowers’ aroma. Its scent deeply relaxes people.

Name: Roselia
FlavorText: A ROSELIA that drinks nutritionally rich springwater blooms with lovely flowers. The fragrance of its flowers has the effect of making its foes careless.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: They swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: These Pokémon have sharp fangs and powerful jaws. Sailors avoid Carvanha dens at all costs.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: It won’t attack while it’s alone—not even if it spots prey. Instead, it waits for other Carvanha to join it, and then the Pokémon attack as a group.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: With its sturdy jaws and fangs, it can easily chomp wooden boats to splinters. It fights with Basculin over food.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: They’re such cowards that they won’t hunt alone. When five or so of them get together, they suddenly turn ferocious!

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: If they scent the faintest trace of blood, they rush to attack en masse. When alone, they’re rather cowardly.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: Each school has its own territory. Any intruders are mercilessly attacked with fangs bared.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: If anything invades Carvanha’s territory, it will swarm and tear at the intruder with its pointed fangs. On its own, however, this Pokémon turns suddenly timid.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: Carvanha’s strongly developed jaws and its sharply pointed fangs pack the destructive power to rip out boat hulls. Many boats have been attacked and sunk by this Pokémon.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: It lives in massive rivers that course through jungles. It swarms prey that enter its territory.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: They form packs to attack boats and rip out their hulls to sink them. They live in rivers in the jungle.

Name: Carvanha
FlavorText: CARVANHA attack ships in swarms, making them sink. Although it is said to be a very vicious POKéMON, it timidly flees as soon as it finds itself alone.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: The moment it charges into its opponent, sharp spikes pop out of Sharpedo’s head, leaving its opponent with deep wounds.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: The yellow patterns it bears are old scars. The energy from Mega Evolution runs through them, causing it sharp pain and suffering.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: As a consequence of Mega Evolution, its combative instincts exploded. The yellow marks it bears are scars from a long history of battles.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: The spines sprouting from its head are transformed fangs. If they’re injured or broken off, the spines will regenerate countless times.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as the Bully of the Sea.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: This Pokémon is known as the Bully of the Sea. Any ship entering the waters Sharpedo calls home will be attacked—no exceptions.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: It drinks in seawater and jets it from its rear to propel itself. It’s very sensitive to the scent of blood.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: People believe that carrying one of its discarded fangs will prevent mishaps at sea, so the fangs are made into accessories.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: It has a sad history. In the past, its dorsal fin was a treasured foodstuff, so this Pokémon became a victim of overfishing.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: It pursues its prey at speeds of 75 mph and finishes them off with fangs that can crush iron. It is known as the bully of the sea.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: Sharpedo can swim at speeds of up to 75 mph by jetting seawater out of its backside. This Pokémon’s drawback is its inability to swim long distances.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: Nicknamed “the bully of the sea,” Sharpedo is widely feared. Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off. Just one of these Pokémon can thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: It can swim at speeds of 75 mph by jetting seawater through its body. It is the bandit of the sea.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as “The Bully of the Sea.”

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: The vicious and sly gangster of the sea. Its skin is specially textured to minimize drag in water. Its speed tops out at over 75 miles per hour.

Name: Sharpedo
FlavorText: The ruffian of the seas, it has fangs that crunch through iron. It swims by jetting water from its rear.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nostrils.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: When it sucks in a large volume of seawater, it becomes like a big, bouncy ball. It eats a ton of food daily.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: Due to their memories of when they once lived on land, pods of them will, very rarely, wash up on shore.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: It swims along with its mouth open and swallows down seawater along with its food. It sprays excess water out of its nostrils.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: It loves to startle people. It fills itself up with seawater and plays by bouncing around like a ball.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: Wailmer can store water inside its body to transform itself into a ball for bouncing around on the ground. By filling itself up with more water, this Pokémon can elevate the height of its bounces.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: Wailmer’s nostrils are located above its eyes. This playful Pokémon loves to startle people by forcefully snorting out seawater it stores inside its body out of its nostrils.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: It eats one ton of food every day. It plays by shooting stored seawater out its blowholes with great force.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: It bounces playfully like a ball. The more seawater it swallows, the higher it bounces.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: On sunny days, it lands on beaches to bounce like a ball and play. It spouts water from its nose.

Name: Wailmer
FlavorText: While this POKéMON usually lives in the sea, it can survive on land, although not too long. It loses vitality if its body becomes dried out.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: It’s the biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: Its immense size is the reason for its popularity. Wailord watching is a favorite sightseeing activity in various parts of the world.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: When a small Wailmer is attacked by Sharpedo or Dhelmise, its whole pod works together to protect it.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: They eat so many fish Pokémon that when Wailord become too numerous, fishermen have to chase them off.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: Wailord pursue their prey in pods. With their large mouths, they can swallow entire schools of Wishiwashi whole.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: When chasing prey, Wailord herds them by leaping out of the water and making a humongous splash. It is breathtaking to see this Pokémon leaping out of the sea with others in its pod.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: Wailord is the largest of all identified Pokémon up to now. This giant Pokémon swims languorously in the vast open sea, eating massive amounts of food at once with its enormous mouth.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: The biggest of all Pokémon. It can dive to a depth of almost 10,000 feet on only one breath.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: It is the largest of all identified Pokémon. They jump as a pack to herd their prey.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: It breathes through nostrils that it raises above the sea. By inhaling to its maximum capacity, a WAILORD can dive close to 10,000 feet beneath the waves.

Name: Wailord
FlavorText: It is among the largest of all POKéMON. It herds prey in a pack then swallows the massed prey in one gulp.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: The flaming magma it stores in the hump on its back is the source of its tremendous power.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: Magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. When it grows cold, the magma hardens and slows it.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing Numel down.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: Numel stores magma of almost 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit within its body. If it gets wet, the magma cools and hardens. In that event, the Pokémon’s body grows heavy and its movements become sluggish.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: Numel is extremely dull witted—it doesn’t notice being hit. However, it can’t stand hunger for even a second. This Pokémon’s body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: The magma in its body reaches 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit. Its hump gets smaller when it uses Fire-type moves.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing its movement.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: The magma in its body reaches 2,200 degrees F. Its hump gets smaller when it uses Fire-type moves.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: A NUMEL stores boiling magma in the hump on its back. It is a hardy POKéMON that can transport a 220-pound load. It has served humans at work since long ago.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: NUMEL stores magma of almost 2,200 degrees F within its body. If it gets wet, the magma cools and hardens. In that event, the POKéMON’s body grows heavy and its movements become sluggish.

Name: Numel
FlavorText: NUMEL is extremely dull witted - it doesn’t notice being hit. However, it can’t stand hunger for even a second. This POKéMON’s body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: If angered, the humps on its back erupt in a shower of molten lava. It lives in the craters of volcanoes.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: It has volcanoes on its back. If magma builds up in its body, it shudders, then erupts violently.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: The humps on Camerupt’s back are formed by a transformation of its bones. They sometimes blast out molten magma. This Pokémon apparently erupts often when it is enraged.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: Camerupt has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this Pokémon’s back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: The volcanoes on its back have a major eruption every 10 years--or whenever it becomes really angry.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: A POKéMON that lives in the crater of a volcano. Every 10 years, the volcanoes on its back erupt violently. Research is under way on the cause of eruption.

Name: Camerupt
FlavorText: CAMERUPT has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees F courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this POKéMON’s back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: Coal is the source of Torkoal’s energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mountains where they live.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is in a tough situation.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: You find abandoned coal mines full of them. They dig tirelessly in search of coal.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: It burns coal to produce energy. When it has burned through all of its coal, it becomes unable to move.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: You can tell how it’s feeling by the smoke spouting from its shell. Tremendous velocity is a sign of good health.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: If the fire burning within its shell goes out, it will die. Those who wish to raise one in their home must always keep something flammable at hand.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: Torkoal generates energy by burning coal. It grows weaker as the fire dies down. When it is preparing for battle, this Pokémon burns more coal.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: Torkoal digs through mountains in search of coal. If it finds some, it fills hollow spaces on its shell with the coal and burns it. If it is attacked, this Pokémon spouts thick black smoke to beat a retreat.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: It battles using energy it gets from burning coal. When loosing smoke from its nostrils, it lets off a sound that is similar to a locomotive’s horn.

Name: Torkoal
FlavorText: It burns coal inside its shell. If it is attacked, it belches thick, black smoke and flees.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: It prefers harsh environments, such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: By storing water in its body, this desert dweller can survive for 30 days without water.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: The more arid and harsh the environment, the more pretty and fragrant a flower Cacnea grows. This Pokémon battles by wildly swinging its thorny arms.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: Cacnea lives in arid locations such as deserts. It releases a strong aroma from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this Pokémon shoots sharp thorns from its body to bring the victim down.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

Name: Cacnea
FlavorText: CACNEA live in deserts with virtually no rainfall. It battles by swinging its thick, spiked arms. Once a year, a yellow flower blooms.

Name: Cacturne
FlavorText: It lives in deserts. It becomes active at night when it hunts for prey exhausted from the desert’s heat.

Name: Cacturne
FlavorText: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.

Name: Cacturne
FlavorText: It becomes active at night, seeking prey that is exhausted from the day’s desert heat.

Name: Cacturne
FlavorText: If a traveler is going through a desert in the thick of night, Cacturne will follow in a ragtag group. The Pokémon are biding their time, waiting for the traveler to tire and become incapable of moving.

Name: Cacturne
FlavorText: During the daytime, Cacturne remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. This Pokémon becomes active at night when the temperature drops.

Name: Cacturne
FlavorText: After spending thousands of years in harsh deserts, its blood transformed into the same substances as sand. It is nocturnal, so it hunts at night.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: It probes muddy riverbeds with its two long whiskers. A slimy film protects its body.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters, it can detect its prey’s location.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Makes its home in swamps with murky water. The poor visibility hides this Pokémon from predators, and the slime on its body makes grasping it difficult.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its whiskers make a superb radar. They are used to locate prey, even in the murkiest of water.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: It coats its entire body with a slimy fluid so it can squirm and slip away if grabbed.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its slimy body is hard to grasp. In one region, it is said to have been born from hardened mud.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its whiskers are filled with nerves. They can sense smells and flavors just as a person’s nose or tongue would.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its entire body is gooey. When pecked at by bird Pokémon, it slips and slides its way to freedom.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its slippery body is hard to grasp, so much so that there are festivals where people compete to see how many they can catch barehanded.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Barboach’s body is covered with a slimy film. If a foe grabs it, this Pokémon just slips out of the enemy’s grip. This Pokémon grows weak if the slimy coating dries up.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Barboach’s sensitive whiskers serve as a superb radar system. This Pokémon hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits for prey to come along.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: BARBOACH uses its whiskers to taste things just as a person uses his or her tongue to taste things.

Name: Barboach
FlavorText: Its body is covered with a slimy film. The film acts as a barrier to prevent germs in muddy water from entering the BARBOACH’s body.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: Sighting Whiscash leaping from the water is believed to herald an earthquake.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: It is extremely protective of its territory. If any foe approaches, it attacks using vicious tremors.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: Strikes its caudal fin against the swamp bed to shake the ground and startle its prey. It will then swallow the fleeing prey whole. People mistook this behavior as the cause of earthquakes.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: As a result of causing tremors by thrashing about, it developed the ability to foretell real quakes.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: It is very territorial. It repels foes by setting off tremors that extend over a three-mile radius.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: It claims a large swamp to itself. If a foe comes near it, it sets off tremors by thrashing around.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything—if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: Its vision is not that good. It senses vibrations in the water with its whiskers to determine the location of its prey.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: Whiscash shakes the ground at high intensities to intimidate its opponents. It swallows its prey whole—along with mud from the swamp floor.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: A glutton that devours anything that moves, it quietly lurks at the bottom of swamps, lying in wait for prey.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: If Whiscash goes on a wild rampage, it sets off a quake-like tremor with a radius of over three miles. This Pokémon has the ability to predict real earthquakes.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: Whiscash is extremely territorial. Just one of these Pokémon will claim a large pond as its exclusive territory. If a foe approaches it, it thrashes about and triggers a massive earthquake.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything--if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: Mysteriously, it can foretell earthquakes. In the daytime, it sleeps in mud at the bottom of a pond. When it awakens, it continually feeds throughout the night.

Name: Whiscash
FlavorText: It makes its nest at the bottom of  swamps. It will eat anything - if it is alive, WHISCASH will eat it.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: Its hardy vitality enables it to adapt to any environment. Its pincers will never release prey.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: It was originally a Pokémon from afar that escaped to the wild. It can adapt to the dirtiest river.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: It can adapt very well to its environment. Feebas and Corphish are about the only Pokémon to live in stagnant ditches.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: Individuals that have been set free by Trainers who could no longer raise them have become common, and they can now be found in Alola.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: Corphish catches prey with its sharp claws. It has no likes or dislikes when it comes to food—it will eat anything. This Pokémon has no trouble living in filthy water.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: Corphish were originally foreign Pokémon that were imported as pets. They eventually turned up in the wild. This Pokémon is very hardy and has greatly increased its population.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: Once it grips prey with its large pincers, it will never let go, no matter what. It is a hardy POKéMON that can thrive in any environment.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: It came from overseas. It is a very hardy creature that will quickly proliferate, even in polluted streams.

Name: Corphish
FlavorText: CORPHISH catches prey with its sharp claws. It has no likes or dislikes when it comes to food - it will eat anything. This POKéMON has no trouble living in filthy water.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: It is a ruffian that uses its pincers to pick up and toss out other Pokémon from its pond.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: A brutish Pokémon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: A rough customer that wildly flails its giant claws. It is said to be extremely hard to raise.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: Its pincers often fall off. Unlike with Crabrawler or Clauncher, the meat in its claws is utterly nasty and stinking.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: Its temperament is rough and it loves to fight, but as soon as its pincers break off, it turns cowardly. It stays timid until they grow back.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: Crawdaunt molts (sheds) its shell regularly. Immediately after molting, its shell is soft and tender. Until the shell hardens, this Pokémon hides in its streambed burrow to avoid attack from its foes.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: Crawdaunt has an extremely violent nature that compels it to challenge other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in ponds inhabited by this Pokémon, making them desolate places.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: Loving to battle, this Pokémon pinches all Pokémon that enter its territory with its pincers and throws them out.

Name: Crawdaunt
FlavorText: A brutish POKéMON that loves to battle. A veteran CRAWDAUNT that has prevailed in hundreds of battles has giant pincers marked with countless scars.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: Lileep clings to rocks on the seabed. When prey comes close, this Pokémon entangles it with petallike tentacles.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Lileep once lived in warm seas that existed approximately 100,000,000 years ago.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: It sticks to rocks with its powerful suckers and can’t be washed away no matter how rough the surf gets.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: In ancient times, it lived in warm seas. It disguised itself as seaweed to ambush its prey and devoured them whole when they got close.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: Lileep is an ancient Pokémon that was regenerated from a fossil. It remains permanently anchored to a rock. From its immobile perch, this Pokémon intently scans for prey with its two eyes.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: Lileep became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. This ancient Pokémon attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles shaped like flower petals.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: It disguises its tentacles as flowers to attract and catch prey. It became extinct in ancient times.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: It disguises itself as seaweed by making its tentacles sway. Unsuspecting prey that come too close are swallowed whole. It became extinct 100 million years ago.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: It became extinct roughly 100 million years ago. It was regenerated from a fossil using advanced techniques.

Name: Lileep
FlavorText: LILEEP became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. This ancient POKéMON attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles  shaped like flower petals.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: Once Cradily catches prey in its tentacles, it digests them whole and absorbs their nutrients.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: It has short legs and can’t walk very fast, but its neck and tentacles can extend to over three times their usual length to nab distant prey.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: This carnivorous Pokémon lived in primordial seas. It catches prey in its eight tentacles and dissolves them with digestive fluid as it eats.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: Normally, it lived on shallow sea shoals. When the tide went out, this Pokémon came up on land to search for prey.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: Cradily’s body serves as an anchor, preventing it from being washed away in rough seas. This Pokémon secretes a strong digestive fluid from its tentacles.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: Cradily roams around the ocean floor in search of food. This Pokémon freely extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight tentacles.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: It ensnares prey with its eight tentacles. It then melts the prey with a strong acid before feeding.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: It lives in warm seas. Its heavy body weighs it down so it won’t get washed away in rough weather.

Name: Cradily
FlavorText: It drags its heavy body along the seafloor. It makes its nest in the shallows of warm seas. CRADILY can be seen on beaches when the tide goes out.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: It eats anything, so it can even live in polluted streams and lakes. No one pays any attention to it.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: They are famous for their shabby appearance. Although populous, they tend to cluster in set locations.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: It is a shabby and ugly Pokémon. However, it is very hardy and can survive on little water.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: Although unattractive and unpopular, this Pokémon’s marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: Because of its wretched appearance, most people pay it no attention, but there are some who collect Feebas—and Feebas alone!

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: They look ragged, so no one catches them. They look like they’d taste bad, so predators won’t eat them. And their numbers continue to grow.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: A tough Pokémon that is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However, due to its ragged, shabby appearance, it isn’t popular.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: While Feebas’s body is in tatters, it has a hardy and tenacious life force that enables it to live anywhere. However, this Pokémon is also slow and dimwitted, making it an easy catch.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: Feebas’s fins are ragged and tattered from the start of its life. Because of its shoddy appearance, this Pokémon is largely ignored. It is capable of living in both the sea and in rivers.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: It is the shabbiest Pokémon of all. It forms in schools and lives at the bottom of rivers.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: It is famous for its shabby appearance. While populous, they tend to cluster in set locations.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: FEEBAS live in ponds that are heavily infested with weeds. Because of its hopelessly shabby appearance, it seems as if few TRAINERS raise it.

Name: Feebas
FlavorText: Ridiculed for its shabby appearance, it is ignored by researchers. It lives in ponds choked with weeds.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: It is the world’s most beautiful Pokémon. There are many works of art featuring Milotic.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: When people bicker, it is said to arise from the depths of lakes to becalm violent hearts.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: It’s said that a glimpse of a Milotic and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you’re feeling.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokémon of all.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: Its dwelling place is the bottom of big lakes. Those who behold its loveliness are said to have their hearts purified.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: While Milotic is said to be the most beautiful Pokémon, Trainers who like Feebas and have raised it are seemingly disappointed by Milotic.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: It lives at the bottom of clear lakes. In times of war, it shows itself, which soothes people’s minds and hearts.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: Milotic live at the bottom of large lakes. When this Pokémon’s body glows a vivid pink, it releases a pulsing wave of energy that brings soothing calm to troubled hearts.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: Milotic is said to be the most beautiful of all the Pokémon. It has the power to becalm such emotions as anger and hostility to quell bitter feuding.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: Milotic is breathtakingly beautiful. Those that see it are said to forget their combative spirits.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: Its lovely scales are described as rainbow colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: It is said to live at the bottom of large lakes. Considered to be the most beautiful of all POKéMON, it has been depicted in paintings and statues.

Name: Milotic
FlavorText: MILOTIC live at the bottom of large lakes. When this POKéMON’s body glows a vivid pink, it releases a pulsing wave of energy that brings soothing calm to restless spirits.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is Castform’s form when pelted by rain. In an experiment where it was placed in a shower, this Pokémon didn’t change to this form.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: Castform changes to this form when rain hits it. Its body is soft and slightly swollen with water.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is Castform’s form during a downpour of rain. Its body retains moisture and gets slippery.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is the form Castform takes when soaked with rain. When its body is compressed, water will seep out as if from a sponge.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: Castform changes to this form when it basks in bright sunlight. When you touch its glowing skin, it feels all dried out!

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is the form Castform takes on bright days. In an experiment where Castform was placed in front of a heater, it didn’t change to this form.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is Castform’s form when basking in fair weather. Its body is warm and toasty.

Name: Castform
FlavorText: This is the form Castform takes on the brightest of days. Its skin is unexpectedly hot to the touch, so approach with care.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: Delicious fruits grew out from around its neck because it always ate the same kind of fruit.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: It lives in tropical jungles. The bunch of fruit around its neck is delicious. The fruit grows twice a year.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: Because it continually ate only its favorite fruit, the fruit started growing around its neck.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: Bunches of delicious fruit grow around its neck. In warm areas, many ranches raise Tropius.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: The bunches of fruit growing around the necks of Tropius in Alola are especially sweet compared to those in other regions.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: Children of the southern tropics eat as snacks the fruit that grows in bunches around the neck of Tropius. This Pokémon flies by flapping the leaves on its back as if they were wings.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: The bunches of fruit around Tropius’s neck are very popular with children. This Pokémon loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for fruit resulted in its own outgrowth of fruit.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It’s a highly favored tropical snack.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: It flies by flapping its broad leaves and gives the sweet, delicious fruit around its neck to children.

Name: Tropius
FlavorText: It flies by flapping its broad leaves. The bunch of fruit that grows around its neck is deliciously sweet. In the spring, it scatters pollen from its neck.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: During the season when drift ice approaches the shore, Spheal prefers living on the ice—where fewer predators lurk—rather than the land. Its fur retains heat superbly and resists harsh cold.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: It rolls across ice floes to reach shore because its body is poorly shaped for swimming.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: As it drifts among the waves, Spheal probes the sea. As soon as it spots prey, it informs the Walrein in its herd.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s body is covered in blubber and impressively round. It’s faster for Spheal to roll around than walk.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: Spheal always travels by rolling around on its ball-like body. When the season for ice floes arrives, this Pokémon can be seen rolling about on ice and crossing the sea.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: Spheal is much faster rolling than walking to get around. When groups of this Pokémon eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this, their mealtimes are noisy.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: Its body is covered in fluffy fur. The fur keeps it from feeling cold while it is rolling on ice.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: They can’t swim well yet, and they move much faster by rolling. When they’re happy, they clap fins.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: It crosses the oceans by rolling itself on drifting ice. Fluffy fur keeps it warm when the temperature is below freezing.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: It is completely covered with plushy fur. As a result, it never feels the cold even when it is rolling about on ice floes or diving in the sea.

Name: Spheal
FlavorText: SPHEAL is much faster rolling than  walking to get around. When groups of this POKéMON eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this, their mealtimes are noisy.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: Its white whiskers are very sensitive. Sealeo will balance Spheal on the tip of its nose, checking its scent and its feel to be sure the Spheal is healthy.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: It habitually spins things on its nose. By doing so, it learns textures and odors.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: This Pokémon has a habit of spinning round things on its nose, whether those things are Poké Balls or Spheal.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: Sealeo live on top of drift ice. They go swimming when they’re on the hunt, seeking out their prey by scent.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: Sealeo often balances and rolls things on the tip of its nose. While the Pokémon is rolling something, it checks the object’s aroma and texture to determine whether it likes the object or not.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: Sealeo has the habit of always juggling on the tip of its nose anything it sees for the first time. This Pokémon occasionally entertains itself by balancing and rolling a Spheal on its nose.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: Be it Spheal or Poké Ball, it will spin any round object on its nose with the greatest of ease.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: It has a very sensitive nose. It touches new things with its nose to examine them.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: SEALEO live in herds on ice floes. Using its powerful flippers, it shatters ice. It dives into the sea to hunt prey five times a day.

Name: Sealeo
FlavorText: It touches new things with its nose to test for smell and feel. It plays by spinning SPHEAL on its nose.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: Its thick tusks are strong enough to shatter drift ice. They have been known to break, but they will grow back by the next year. The Hisui region is well known for these broken tusks.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: It shatters ice with its big tusks. Its thick blubber repels not only the cold but also enemy attacks.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: Walrein’s tusks keep growing throughout its life. Tusks broken in battle will grow back to their usual impressive size in a year.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: Walrein form herds of 20 to 30 individuals. When a threat appears, the herd’s leader will protect the group with its life.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: Walrein swims all over in frigid seawater while crushing icebergs with its grand, imposing tusks. Its thick layer of blubber makes enemy attacks bounce off harmlessly.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: Walrein’s two massively developed tusks can totally shatter blocks of ice weighing 10 tons with one blow. This Pokémon’s thick coat of blubber insulates it from subzero temperatures.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: It shatters drift ice with its strong tusks. Its thick layer of blubber repels enemy attacks.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: It shatters ice with its big tusks. Its thick blubber repels not only the cold, but also enemy attacks.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: Not only does its thick blubber keep it warm, it also protects it from attacks. It shatters ice with its prized tusks.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: To protect its herd, the leader battles anything that invades its territory, even at the cost of its life. Its tusks may snap off in battle.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: It swims through icy seas while shattering ice floes with its large tusks. It is protected by its thick blubber.

Name: Walrein
FlavorText: WALREIN’s two massively developed tusks can totally shatter blocks of ice weighing ten tons with one blow. This POKéMON’s thick coat of blubber insulates it from subzero temperatures.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: Clamperl’s pearls are exceedingly precious. They can be more than 10 times as costly as Shellder’s pearls.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: Despite its appearance, it’s carnivorous. It clamps down on its prey with both sides of its shell and doesn’t let go until they stop moving.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: Clamperl grows while being protected by its rock-hard shell. When its body becomes too large to fit inside the shell, it is sure evidence that this Pokémon is getting close to evolution.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: Clamperl’s sturdy shell is not only good for protection—it is also used for clamping and catching prey. A fully grown Clamperl’s shell will be scored with nicks and scratches all over.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: It is protected by a sturdy shell. Once in a lifetime, it makes a magnificent pearl.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: When it evolves, it makes a mysterious pearl that amplifies psychic powers when it’s held.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: A CLAMPERL slams its shell closed on prey to prevent escape. The pearl it creates upon evolution is said to be infused with a mysterious energy.

Name: Clamperl
FlavorText: CLAMPERL’s sturdy shell is not only good for protection - it is also used for clamping and catching prey. A fully grown CLAMPERL’s shell will be scored with nicks and scratches all over.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: Deep seas are their habitat. According to tradition, when Huntail wash up onshore, something unfortunate will happen.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: It’s not the strongest swimmer. It wags its tail to lure in its prey and then gulps them down as soon as they get close.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: Huntail’s tail is shaped like a fish. It uses the tail to attract prey, then swallows the prey whole with its large, gaping mouth. This Pokémon swims by wiggling its slender body like a snake.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: Huntail’s presence went unnoticed by people for a long time because it lives at extreme depths in the sea. This Pokémon’s eyes can see clearly even in the murky dark depths of the ocean.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: It lives deep in the sea where no light ever filters down. It lights up its small fishlike tail to attract prey.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: It lives deep in the pitch-dark sea. It attracts prey by moving its tail in mimicry of a small animal.

Name: Huntail
FlavorText: To withstand the crushing pressure of water deep under the sea, its spine is very thick and sturdy. Its tail, which is shaped like a small fish, has eyes that light up.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: It sucks bodily fluids out of its prey. The leftover meat sinks to the seafloor, where it becomes food for other Pokémon.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: The color of its body changes with the water temperature. The coloration of Gorebyss in Alola is almost blindingly vivid.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: Although Gorebyss is the very picture of elegance and beauty while swimming, it is also cruel. When it spots prey, this Pokémon inserts its thin mouth into the prey’s body and drains the prey of its body fluids.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: Gorebyss lives in the southern seas at extreme depths. Its body is built to withstand the enormous pressure of water at incredible depths. Because of this, this Pokémon’s body is unharmed by ordinary attacks.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant. With its thin mouth, it feeds on seaweed that grows between rocks.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: Its pink body becomes more vivid with the rise of water temperatures in the springtime.

Name: Gorebyss
FlavorText: A GOREBYSS siphons the body fluids of prey through its thin, tubular mouth. Its light pink body color turns vivid when it finishes feeding.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: This rare Pokémon was discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: This Pokémon was discovered during deep-sea exploration. Its appearance hasn’t changed in 100,000,000 years, so it’s called a living fossil.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokémon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: The reason it hasn’t changed at all in a hundred million years is that it’s apparently already a perfect life-form.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: Thought to have gone extinct, Relicanth was given a name that is a variation of the name of the person who discovered it.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: It was fortuitously discovered during a deep sea expedition. Its teeth have atrophied, so it now survives on microscopic organisms it sucks up.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: Its form has remained the same for one hundred million years. Its body is filled with fat, so it can withstand the water pressure of the deep sea.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: Relicanth is a rare species that was discovered in deep-sea explorations. This Pokémon’s body withstands the enormous water pressure of the ocean depths. Its body is covered in tough scales that are like craggy rocks.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: Relicanth is a Pokémon species that existed for a hundred million years without ever changing its form. This ancient Pokémon feeds on microscopic organisms with its toothless mouth.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: A rare Pokémon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: It has remained unchanged for 100 million years. It was discovered during a deep-sea exploration.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: Discovered by chance during deep-sea explorations, it has not changed since ancient times.

Name: Relicanth
FlavorText: A POKéMON that was once believed to have been extinct. The species has not changed its form for 100 million years. It walks on the seafloor using its pectoral fins.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: Its heart-shaped body makes it popular. In some places, you would give a Luvdisc to someone you love.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: It lives in warm seas. It is said that couples who find this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: Luvdisc makes its home in coral reefs in warm seas. It especially likes sleeping in the space between Corsola’s branches.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: There was an era when it was overfished due to the rumor that having one of its heart-shaped scales would enable you to find a sweetheart.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: Loving couples have a soft spot for this Pokémon, so honeymoon hotels often release this Pokémon into their pools.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: If a Luvdisc is left on its own, it becomes despondent, leaving itself open to attack. That is when Pelipper snatch them up.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: Luvdisc’s heart-shaped body is a symbol of love and romance. It is said that any couple meeting this Pokémon is promised a loving relationship that never ends.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: Luvdisc live in shallow seas in the tropics. This heart-shaped Pokémon earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the ocean’s waves.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.

Name: Luvdisc
FlavorText: LUVDISC make the branches of CORSOLA their nests. There is a custom from long ago of giving a LUVDISC as a gift to express one’s feelings of love.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: Through Primal Reversion and with nature’s full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: A mythical Pokémon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with Groudon.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: KYOGRE has appeared in mythology as the creator of the sea. After long years of feuding with GROUDON, it took to sleep at the bottom of the sea.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: This POKéMON is said to have expanded the sea by bringing heavy rains. It has the power to control water.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: KYOGRE is named in mythology as the POKéMON that expanded the sea by covering the land with torrential rains and towering tidal waves. It took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with GROUDON.

Name: Kyogre
FlavorText: KYOGRE has the power to create massive rain clouds that cover the entire sky and bring about torrential downpours. This POKéMON saved people who were suffering from droughts.

Name: Turtwig
FlavorText: This Pokémon becomes more energetic the more sunlight there is. The part resembling a shell is similar to silt and is slightly damp and warm to the touch.

Name: Turtwig
FlavorText: It undertakes photosynthesis within its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if the Pokémon is thirsty.

Name: Turtwig
FlavorText: Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.

Name: Turtwig
FlavorText: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

Name: Turtwig
FlavorText: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.

Name: Turtwig
FlavorText: The shell on its back is made of soil. On a very healthy Turtwig, the shell should feel moist.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: Appears where there is clean spring water. The fruit that grows on the shrubs on its shell is sweet, nutritious, and truly delicious.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: Its shell is hardened soil. Some Pokémon come to peck the berries growing on the trees on its back.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe the trees on its shell.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: A GROTLE that lives in the forest is said to have its own secret springwater.

Name: Grotle
FlavorText: The shell is hardened soil. Some Pokémon come to peck the berries growing on the trees on its back.

Name: Torterra
FlavorText: This remarkable, large-bodied Pokémon would serve beautifully as borrowed scenery for a garden, and its strength is peerless. Torterra roams the wilderness in search of clean water.

Name: Torterra
FlavorText: Groups of this Pokémon migrating in search of water have been mistaken for moving forests.

Name: Torterra
FlavorText: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

Name: Torterra
FlavorText: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground, a gigantic Torterra dwelled.

Name: Torterra
FlavorText: Some Pokémon are born on a Torterra’s back and spend their entire life there.

Name: Torterra
FlavorText: Groups of this Pokémon migrating in search of water have been mistaken for “moving forests.”

Name: Chimchar
FlavorText: Full of vigor and always in high spirits. It was once known by the name “Lantern-Tail” and feared as some kind of apparition.

Name: Chimchar
FlavorText: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can’t extinguish the fire.

Name: Chimchar
FlavorText: It agilely scales sheer cliffs to live atop craggy mountains. Its fire is put out when it sleeps.

Name: Chimchar
FlavorText: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

Name: Chimchar
FlavorText: It is very agile. Before going to sleep, it extinguishes the flame on its tail to prevent fires.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: The deeper the blue on its face, the more powerful it will grow to become. It leaps about every which way and lands powerful blows against its opponents with the flame on its tail.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one of its weapons.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: To intimidate attackers, it expands the fire on its tail to make itself appear bigger.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: A bigger fire on its tail and a brighter blue pattern on its face means its rank in its pack is higher.

Name: Monferno
FlavorText: To intimidate attackers, it stretches the fire on its tail to make itself appear bigger.

Name: Infernape
FlavorText: A tall, hardy Pokémon with a dazzling appearance. It shrouds itself in flame and battles as if engaged in dance—truly a sight to behold.

Name: Infernape
FlavorText: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

Name: Infernape
FlavorText: It uses a special kind of martial arts involving all its limbs. Its fire never goes out.

Name: Infernape
