FlavorText: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.

Name: Fennekin
FlavorText: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Braixen
FlavorText: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.

Name: Braixen
FlavorText: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

Name: Delphox
FlavorText: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.

Name: Delphox
FlavorText: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

Name: Froakie
FlavorText: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

Name: Froakie
FlavorText: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

Name: Frogadier
FlavorText: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute’s time.

Name: Frogadier
FlavorText: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

Name: Greninja
FlavorText: It appears and vanishes with a ninja’s grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

Name: Greninja
FlavorText: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: Its territory has a radius of just over a mile. If any bird Pokémon should enter, it will show them no mercy.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: Fletchinder scatters embers in tall grass where bug Pokémon might be hiding and then catches them as they come leaping out.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: Fletchinder are exceedingly territorial and aggressive. These Pokémon fight among themselves over feeding grounds.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: Fletchinder launches embers into the den of its prey. When the prey comes leaping out, Fletchinder’s sharp talons finish it off.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: Its speed right after takeoff already puts it in the top speed class of all bird Pokémon.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: It scatters embers in the tall grass. Then bug Pokémon, frightened by the flames, come flying out, and Fletchinder gobbles them up.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: It will not tolerate other Fletchinder entering its territory, which has a radius of several miles.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: From its beak, it fires embers at its prey. Once it has caught them, it grills them at high heat before feasting upon them.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: The hotter the flame sac on its belly, the faster it can fly, but it takes some time to get the fire going.

Name: Fletchinder
FlavorText: From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: When it gets excited, it vents sparks from the gaps between its feathers. These unburnable feathers are used as a fireproof material.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: It has top-notch flying capabilities. It flies around easily, even while carrying prey that weighs more than 220 lbs.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: Talonflame dives toward prey at speeds of up to 310 mph and assaults them with powerful kicks, giving the prey no chance to escape.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: Talonflame mainly preys upon other bird Pokémon. To intimidate opponents, it sends embers spewing from gaps between its feathers.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: Bird Pokémon make up most of its diet. It approaches at high speeds and smacks them down to the ground with its powerful kick.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: Its tough wings don’t allow fire to pass through them. A long time ago, firefighters’ outfits were made from Talonflame wings.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: It zooms directly at its prey at flight speeds of close to 310 mph, while fiery embers scatter from gaps in its feathers.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: Its favorite foods are Wingull and Pikipek. It attacks with a powerful kick and grasps them firmly in its talons.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: When attacking prey, it can reach speeds of up to 310 mph. It finishes its prey off with a colossal kick.

Name: Talonflame
FlavorText: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.

Name: Litleo
FlavorText: The more a Litleo trains its body and spirit by battling mighty enemies, the hotter its mane will grow.

Name: Litleo
FlavorText: When Litleo are young, female Pyroar will teach them how to hunt. Once the Litleo mature, they will leave the pride and set out on their own.

Name: Litleo
FlavorText: This hot-blooded Pokémon is filled with curiosity. When it gets angry or starts fighting, its short mane gets hot.

Name: Litleo
FlavorText: When they’re young, they live with a pride. Once they’re able to hunt prey on their own, they’re kicked out and have to make their own way.

Name: Litleo
FlavorText: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.

Name: Litleo
FlavorText: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.

Name: Pyroar
FlavorText: The mane of a male Pyroar heats up to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit during battle. Merely approaching it will cause severe burns.

Name: Pyroar
FlavorText: The females of a pride work together to bring down prey. It’s thanks to them that their pride doesn’t starve.

Name: Pyroar
FlavorText: The temperature of its breath is over 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, but Pyroar doesn’t use it on its prey. This Pokémon prefers to eat raw meat.

Name: Pyroar
FlavorText: The males are usually lazy, but when attacked by a strong foe, a male will protect its friends with no regard for its own safety.

Name: Pyroar
FlavorText: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride’s cubs.

Name: Pyroar
FlavorText: The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.

Name: Skiddo
FlavorText: As long as it has sunlight and water, Skiddo can make energy with the leaves on its body, allowing it to live on rocky mountains barren of food.

Name: Skiddo
FlavorText: Until recently, people living in the mountains would ride on the backs of these Pokémon to traverse the mountain paths.

Name: Skiddo
FlavorText: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn’t need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.

Name: Skiddo
FlavorText: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

Name: Gogoat
FlavorText: These Pokémon live in herds in mountainous places. The victor in their contests of clashing horns will become the leader of the herd.

Name: Gogoat
FlavorText: It can sense the feelings of others by touching them with its horns. This species has assisted people with their work since 5,000 years ago.

Name: Gogoat
FlavorText: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.

Name: Gogoat
FlavorText: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

Name: Binacle
FlavorText: If the two don’t work well together, both their offense and defense fall apart. Without good teamwork, they won’t survive.

Name: Binacle
FlavorText: After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.

Name: Binacle
FlavorText: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.

Name: Binacle
FlavorText: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.

Name: Barbaracle
FlavorText: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. In a pinch, its limbs start to act on their own to ensure the enemy’s defeat.

Name: Barbaracle
FlavorText: Seven Binacle come together to form one Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head gives orders to those serving as the limbs.

Name: Barbaracle
FlavorText: Barbaracle’s legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head’s orders.

Name: Barbaracle
FlavorText: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: This Pokémon is a poor swimmer. If it’s caught in a fierce storm, it will sometimes get washed far away and become unable to return to its home.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: Skrelp evades its enemies by hiding amid drifting seaweed. It eats rotten seaweed to create its poison.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: Skrelp looks like a piece of rotten seaweed, so it can blend in with seaweed drifting on the ocean and avoid being detected by enemies.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: It drifts in the ocean, blending in with floating seaweed. When other Pokémon come to feast on the seaweed, Skrelp feasts on them instead.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: It’s not good at swimming, so it clings to the seaweed. In the Alola region, it’s often found near Dhelmise.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: It vanishes into seaweed and remains perfectly still to avoid attacks from large Pokémon. Rotten seaweed is its main food source.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: It looks just like rotten kelp. It hides from foes while storing up power for its evolution.

Name: Skrelp
FlavorText: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: Clauncher’s claws will regrow if they fall off. The meat inside the claws is edible, but it has a distinct flavor that doesn’t appeal to all tastes.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: This Pokémon launches water by detonating gas inside its right claw. It snipes flying Pokémon.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: By detonating gas that accumulates in its right claw, this Pokémon launches water like a bullet. This is how Clauncher defeats its enemies.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: Clauncher’s claws can fall off during battle, but they’ll regenerate. The meat inside the claws is popular as a delicacy in Galar.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: It moves around by jetting water from its right pincer. It has a poor sense of balance, so it’s terrible at swimming straight.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: Its claws occasionally fall off, and it keeps a low profile until they grow back. The meat of its claws is so delicious!

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: Through controlled explosions of internal gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot. At close distances, it can shatter rock.

Name: Clauncher
FlavorText: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: The cannonballs of seawater that Clawitzer launches from its claw are powerful enough to punch through tanker hulls.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: Clawitzer can move through the water at a speed of 60 knots by using gas inside its body to expel water from the back of its claw.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: Clawitzer’s right arm is a cannon that launches projectiles made of seawater. Shots from a Clawitzer’s cannon arm can sink a tanker.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: After using the feelers on its oversized claw to detect the location of prey, Clawitzer launches a cannonball of water at its target.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: Its right arm is packed with meat. When its pincer falls off, it’s exported to be used as a cooking ingredient.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: It compresses the water it has sucked up and then projects it with enough power to punch a hole right through a thick sheet of iron.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.

Name: Clawitzer
FlavorText: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: With a voice like a human child’s, it cries out to lure adults deep into the forest, getting them lost among the trees.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: After a lost child perished in the forest, their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing the spirit’s rebirth as this Pokémon.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: An unknown spirit came to lodge in a tree stump, creating this Pokémon. A cure-all can be made from an infusion of its green leaves.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: By imitating the voice of a child, it causes people to get hopelessly lost deep in the forest. It’s trying to make friends with them.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: According to legend, medicine to cure any illness can be made by plucking the green leaves on its head, brewing them, and boiling down the liquid.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: These Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died in the forest. Their cries sound like eerie screams.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: According to old tales, these Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died while lost in the forest.

Name: Phantump
FlavorText: These Pokémon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: Small roots that extend from the tips of this Pokémon’s feet can tie into the trees of the forest and give Trevenant control over them.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: People fear it due to a belief that it devours any who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the Pokémon it shares its woods with, it’s kind.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: This Pokémon controls trees via roots stretching from its feet, and it will attack anyone that dares to ravage the forest.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: It’s feared as a ghost of the forest. Lumberjacks bring along Fire types, which Trevenant hates, when they enter the forest.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: Through its roots, it exerts control over other trees. A deadly curse falls upon anyone cutting down trees in forests where Trevenant dwell.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: This Pokémon is said to devour anyone daring to ravage the forest. To the creatures dwelling in the forest, it offers great kindness.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: Using its roots as a nervous system, it controls the trees in the forest. It’s kind to the Pokémon that reside in its body.

Name: Trevenant
FlavorText: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: Massive Pumpkaboo are said to be the product of areas where a great number of lost souls lingered.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: Supersized Pumpkaboo are very partial to the spirits of people who were of similarly superior proportions.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: Large Pumpkaboo are said to be the product of areas where many lost souls lingered.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: When taking spirits to the afterlife, large Pumpkaboo prefer the spirits of adults to those of children.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: Small Pumpkaboo are said to be the product of areas where few lost souls lingered.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: When taking spirits to the afterlife, small Pumpkaboo prefer the spirits of children to those of adults.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: The light that streams out from the holes in the pumpkin can hypnotize and control the people and Pokémon that see it.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: Spirits that wander this world are placed into Pumpkaboo’s body. They’re then moved on to the afterlife.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: It is said to carry wandering spirits to the place where they belong so they can move on.

Name: Pumpkaboo
FlavorText: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: A supersized Pumpkaboo evolves into a supersized Gourgeist. Its bodily proportions also get passed on to its descendants.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: Supersized Gourgeist aren’t picky. They will forcefully drag anyone off to the afterlife.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: A large-sized Pumpkaboo evolves into a large-sized Gourgeist. Its bodily proportions also get passed on to its descendants.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: Large Gourgeist put on the guise of adults, taking the hands of children to lead them to the afterlife.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: A small-sized Pumpkaboo evolves into a small-sized Gourgeist. Its bodily proportions also get passed on to its descendants.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: Small Gourgeist pretend to be children to fool adults. Anyone who falls for the act gets carried away to the hereafter.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: In the darkness of a new-moon night, Gourgeist will come knocking. Whoever answers the door will be swept off to the afterlife.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: Eerie cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are suffering in the afterlife.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.

Name: Gourgeist
FlavorText: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: Flies noiselessly on delicate wings. It has mastered the art of deftly launching dagger-sharp feathers from those same wings.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: During the day, it builds up energy via photosynthesis. At night, it flies silently through the sky, on the prowl for prey.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: At a distance, it launches its sharp feathers while flying about. If the enemy gets too close, Rowlet switches tactics and delivers vicious kicks.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: It feels relaxed in tight, dark places and has been known to use its Trainer’s pocket or bag as a nest.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: It sends its feathers, which are as sharp as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong, so its kicks are also formidable.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: Silently it glides, drawing near its targets. Before they even notice it, it begins to pelt them with vicious kicks.

Name: Rowlet
FlavorText: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: Regularly basks in sunlight to gather power—presumably due to the frigid climate. Nonetheless, the edges of the blade quills set into its wings are keen as ever.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: It never slacks when it comes to the task of cleaning its feathers. Thorough preening keeps it looking spiffy and its blade quills nice and sharp.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: It throws one knifelike feather after another at its enemies, and each one precisely strikes a weak point. These feathers are known as blade quills.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: Supremely sensitive to the presence of others, it can detect opponents standing behind it, flinging its sharp feathers to take them out.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you don’t groom it diligently, it will stop listening to you.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: It throws sharp feathers called blade quills at enemies or prey. It seldom misses.

Name: Dartrix
FlavorText: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: The air stored inside the rachises of Decidueye’s feathers insulates the Pokémon against Hisui’s extreme cold. This is firm proof that evolution can be influenced by environment.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: In a tenth of a second, it can nock and fire an arrow quill, piercing an opponent’s weak point before they notice what’s happening.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye’s shots never miss.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: Decidueye can nock and fire an arrow at an enemy in a tenth of a second, so its battles are decided in the blink of an eye.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: It nocks its arrow quills and shoots them at opponents. When it simply can’t afford to miss, it tugs the vine on its head to improve its focus.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: Although basically cool and cautious, when it’s caught by surprise, it’s seized by panic.

Name: Decidueye
FlavorText: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.

Name: Litten
FlavorText: Trying to pet Litten before it trusts you will result in a nasty scratch from its sharp claws. Be careful.

Name: Litten
FlavorText: It spends even the smallest amount of downtime grooming its fur with its tongue. Loose fur gathers in its stomach and serves as fuel for fiery moves.

Name: Litten
FlavorText: Its coat regrows twice a year. When the time comes, Litten sets its own body on fire and burns away the old fur.

Name: Litten
FlavorText: If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t open up to you. Even if you do grow close, giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

Name: Litten
FlavorText: It doesn’t allow its emotions to be easily seen. Earning its trust takes time. It prefers solitude.

Name: Litten
FlavorText: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

Name: Torracat
FlavorText: When facing a powerful enemy, Torracat’s fighting spirit gets pumped up, and its fire bell blazes hotter.

Name: Torracat
FlavorText: In the midst of battle, the fire pouch on Torracat’s neck rings like a bell and produces stronger flames than usual.

Name: Torracat
FlavorText: When its mane is standing on end, you can tell it’s feeling good. When it isn’t feeling well, its fur will lie down flat.

Name: Torracat
FlavorText: It can act spoiled if it grows close to its Trainer. A powerful Pokémon, its sharp claws can leave its Trainer’s whole body covered in scratches.

Name: Torracat
FlavorText: It boasts powerful front legs. With a single punch, it can bend an iron bar right over.

Name: Torracat
FlavorText: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.

Name: Incineroar
FlavorText: Incineroar’s rough and aggressive behavior is its most notable trait, but the way it helps out small Pokémon shows that it has a kind side as well.

Name: Incineroar
FlavorText: It excels at violent, no-holds-barred battles. The temperature of the flames that issue from its navel exceeds 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Incineroar
FlavorText: When its fighting spirit is set alight, the flames around its waist become especially intense.

Name: Incineroar
FlavorText: Although it’s rough mannered and egotistical, it finds beating down unworthy opponents boring. It gets motivated for stronger opponents.

Name: Incineroar
FlavorText: After hurling ferocious punches and flinging furious kicks, it finishes opponents off by spewing fire from around its navel.

Name: Incineroar
FlavorText: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it’s not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer’s orders with complete nonchalance.

Name: Popplio
FlavorText: If Popplio want to create big, powerful balloons, they must be persistent. It takes daily practice for these Pokémon to develop their skills.

Name: Popplio
FlavorText: It creates special bouncy balloons to send at its opponents. When the balloons pop, the sheer force of their bursting is what deals damage.

Name: Popplio
FlavorText: Popplio gets on top of its bouncy water balloons to jump higher. It’s quite the acrobatic fighter!

Name: Popplio
FlavorText: The balloons it inflates with its nose grow larger and larger as it practices day by day.

Name: Popplio
FlavorText: This Pokémon can control water bubbles. It practices diligently so it can learn to make big bubbles.

Name: Popplio
FlavorText: This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It’s famous for being a hard worker.

Name: Brionne
FlavorText: On nights when the sea is calm, Brionne dance with one another to the singing of the Primarina that’s leading them.

Name: Brionne
FlavorText: As if dancing, it artfully dodges the attacks of its enemies. All the while, it’s busy forming a bunch of balloons to overwhelm its foes.

Name: Brionne
FlavorText: It attacks by smacking its enemies with the exploding water balloons that it creates.

Name: Brionne
FlavorText: It gets excited when it sees a dance it doesn’t know. This hard worker practices diligently until it can learn that dance.

Name: Brionne
FlavorText: It cares deeply for its companions. When its Trainer is feeling down, it performs a cheery dance to try and help.

Name: Brionne
FlavorText: A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, and briskly bombards its enemies.

Name: Primarina
FlavorText: For Primarina, every battle’s a stage. Its singing and the dancing of its balloons will mesmerize the audience.

Name: Primarina
FlavorText: With its mouth, it makes sonic waves that sound like beautiful singing. It uses the sonic waves to control its water balloons.

Name: Primarina
FlavorText: Also known as a songstress, it has a fantastical look on moonlit nights when it leads its colony in song.

Name: Primarina
FlavorText: To Primarina, every battle is a stage. It takes down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.

Name: Primarina
FlavorText: Its singing voice is its chief weapon in battle. This Pokémon’s Trainer must prioritize the daily maintenance of its throat at all costs.

Name: Primarina
FlavorText: It controls its water balloons with song. The melody is learned from others of its kind and is passed down from one generation to the next.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This form of Oricorio has sipped red nectar. It whips up blazing flames as it moves to the steps of its passionate dance.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Pokémon is incredibly popular, possibly because its passionate dancing is a great match with the temperament of Paldean people.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: It wins the hearts of its enemies with its passionate dancing and then uses the opening it creates to burn them up with blazing flames.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: This Oricorio has sipped red nectar. Its passionate dance moves cause its enemies to combust in both body and mind.

Name: Oricorio
FlavorText: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: When facing tough opponents, they get into formation. But if they get wounded in battle, they’ll scatter and become solitary again.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: On their own, they’re very weak. But when Wishiwashi pool their power together in a school, they become a demon of the sea.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: Called “demon of the sea” by some, when Wishiwashi are injured in battle and their numbers dwindle, they become a regular school.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: Wishiwashi assemble in this formation to face off against strong foes. It boasts a strength that earned it the name “demon of the sea.”

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: At their appearance, even Gyarados will flee. When they team up to use Water Gun, its power exceeds that of Hydro Pump.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: Weak Wishiwashi school together to concentrate their power. Their united force makes them the demon of the sea, feared near and far.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: When it senses danger, its eyes tear up. The sparkle of its tears signals other Wishiwashi to gather.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: Individually, they’re incredibly weak. It’s by gathering up into schools that they’re able to confront opponents.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: When it’s in a jam, its shining eyes attract others of its kind. The light from its eyes is visible almost 25 miles away.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: They’re weak, so they move in schools. However, they can also often be seen all alone, having strayed from the school.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: It’s awfully weak and notably tasty, so everyone is always out to get it. As it happens, anyone trying to bully it receives a painful lesson.

Name: Wishiwashi
FlavorText: When it’s in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: It has excellent regenerative capabilities. Legs that a Mareanie has lost have a very bitter, astringent flavor—they’re not suitable as food.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: This Pokémon wanders the seaside looking for food. It often gets electric shocks from broken Pincurchin spines that it tries to eat.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: Unlike their Alolan counterparts, the Mareanie of the Galar region have not yet figured out that the branches of Corsola are delicious.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: The first symptom of its sting is numbness. The next is an itching sensation so intense that it’s impossible to resist the urge to claw at your skin.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: Aside from its head, its body parts regenerate quickly if they’re cut off. After a good night’s sleep, Mareanie is back to normal.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: They eat Corsola branches, so Mareanie are hated by craftsmen who work with Corsola branches that have naturally fallen off.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: It’s found crawling on beaches and seafloors. The coral that grows on Corsola’s head is as good as a five-star banquet to this Pokémon.

Name: Mareanie
FlavorText: It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: Toxapex gets into fierce battles with Bruxish over areas where warm ocean currents flow, but the odds are always against it.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: This Pokémon lives within a dome made by its own legs. Toxapex monitors its surroundings by sensing the flow of the tide through its spikes.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: Within the poison sac in its body is a poison so toxic that Pokémon as large as Wailord will still be suffering three days after it first takes effect.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: To survive in the cold waters of Galar, this Pokémon forms a dome with its legs, enclosing its body so it can capture its own body heat.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: With its 12 legs, it creates a dome to shelter within. The flow of the tides doesn’t affect Toxapex in there, so it’s very comfortable.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: To attack, this Pokémon sends toxic spikes flying at its enemies. Ones that come close get mown down by the claws on its feet.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: Those attacked by Toxapex’s poison will suffer intense pain for three days and three nights. Post-recovery, there will be some aftereffects.

Name: Toxapex
FlavorText: Toxapex crawls along the ocean floor on its 12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits scattered in its wake.

Name: Dewpider
FlavorText: Dewpider normally lives underwater. When it comes onto land in search of food, it takes water with it in the form of a bubble on its head.

Name: Dewpider
FlavorText: It forms a water bubble at the rear of its body and then covers its head with it. Meeting another Dewpider means comparing water-bubble sizes.

Name: Dewpider
FlavorText: It can only breathe oxygen that has dissolved in water, so it wears a water bubble on its head when it walks around on land.

Name: Dewpider
FlavorText: When two Dewpider meet, they display their water bubbles to each other. Then the one with the smaller bubble gets out of the other’s way.

Name: Dewpider
FlavorText: When it comes across enemies or potential prey, this Pokémon smashes its water-bubble-covered head into them.

Name: Dewpider
FlavorText: It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.

Name: Araquanid
FlavorText: It acts as a caretaker for Dewpider, putting them inside its bubble and letting them eat any leftover food.

Name: Araquanid
FlavorText: It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowning prey within the bubbles. This Pokémon can then take its time to savor its meal.

Name: Araquanid
FlavorText: It has a habit of storing things it values in its water bubble. If its Trainer doesn’t watch out, Araquanid will try to put them in its bubble!

Name: Araquanid
FlavorText: It usually passes its time in the water. When its belly is full, it stores its subdued prey in the water bubble on its head.

Name: Araquanid
FlavorText: Despite what its appearance suggests, it cares for others. If it finds vulnerable, weak Pokémon, it protectively brings them into its water bubble.

Name: Araquanid
FlavorText: It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokémon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: Many Trainers give their Fomantis their own flowerpots so they can sunbathe in peace and quiet.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: Fomantis hates having its naps interrupted. It fires off beams using energy it gathers by bathing in the sun.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: During the day, Fomantis basks in sunlight and sleeps peacefully. It wakes and moves around at night.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: When bathed in sunlight, this Pokémon emits a pleasantly sweet scent, which causes bug Pokémon to gather around it.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: It loves the sunshine. When it basks in the sunlight regularly, it grows up with vivid coloration.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: When the sun rises, Fomantis spreads its four leaves and bathes in the sunlight. The tip of its head has a pleasant aroma.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: They give off a sweet and refreshing scent. Cutiefly often gather near the tall grass where Fomantis are hiding.

Name: Fomantis
FlavorText: During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light. When night falls, it walks around looking for a safer place to sleep.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: A lot of time and effort is required to maintain the vivid colors of its petals. This Pokémon puts its Trainer’s attentiveness to the test.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: By masquerading as a bug Pokémon, it lowers the guard of actual bug Pokémon lured in by a scent of sweet flowers. Its sickles bring them down.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: The petals on this Pokémon’s arms are thin and super sharp, and they can fire laser beams if Lurantis gathers light first.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: This Pokémon resembles a beautiful flower. A properly raised Lurantis will have gorgeous, brilliant colors.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: As it slashes into its enemies, it looks like it’s dancing. Its elegant appearance has led some to call it the most glamorous Grass Pokémon.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: For self-protection, it pretends to be a bug Pokémon. Both of its arms bear keen-edged petals.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: It fires beams from its sickle-shaped petals. These beams are powerful enough to cleave through thick metal plates.

Name: Lurantis
FlavorText: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantis’s vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.

Name: Morelull
FlavorText: Morelull live in forests that stay dark even during the day. They scatter flickering spores that put enemies to sleep.

Name: Morelull
FlavorText: Pokémon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull’s head. The caps regrow overnight.

Name: Morelull
FlavorText: It likes damp dark places. When night falls, the spores filling the caps of its mushrooms glow.

Name: Morelull
FlavorText: It scatters its shining spores around itself. Even though they’re dangerous, nighttime tours of forests where Morelull live are popular.

Name: Morelull
FlavorText: As it drowses the day away, it nourishes itself by sucking from tree roots. It wakens at the fall of night, wandering off in search of a new tree.

Name: Morelull
FlavorText: It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.

Name: Shiinotic
FlavorText: If you see a light deep in a forest at night, don’t go near. Shiinotic will make you fall fast asleep.

Name: Shiinotic
FlavorText: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

Name: Shiinotic
FlavorText: When it starts fighting for territory with Parasect, the entire area gets completely coated in spores!

Name: Shiinotic
FlavorText: It puts its prey to sleep and siphons off their vitality through the tip of its arms. If one of its kind is weakened, it helps by sending it vitality.

Name: Shiinotic
FlavorText: It emits flickering spores that cause drowsiness. When its prey succumb to sleep, this Pokémon feeds on them by sucking in their energy.

Name: Shiinotic
FlavorText: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People confused by its strange lights can never find their way home again.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: Only female Salandit can produce gas laden with pheromones. Males entranced by this gas will do whatever the females tell them.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow, rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: This sneaky Pokémon will slink behind its prey and immobilize it with poisonous gas before the prey even realizes Salandit is there.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: Its venom sacs produce a fluid that this Pokémon then heats up with the flame in its tail. This process creates Salandit’s poisonous gas.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: It weakens opponents and sends them reeling with its poisonous gas. Salandit doesn’t deal well with Spinda, since it’s always reeling.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: The males will do whatever the females tell them. They give the females most of their food. Due to malnutrition, the males can’t evolve.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: Volcanoes or dry, craggy places are its home. It emanates a sweet-smelling poisonous gas that attracts bug Pokémon, then attacks them.

Name: Salandit
FlavorText: It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: When two Salazzle meet, they will use their pheromone gas to fight over the males in each other’s group.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring movements to turn them into loyal servants.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: The winner of competitions between Salazzle is decided by which one has the most male Salandit with it.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: Only female Salazzle exist. They emit a gas laden with pheromones to captivate male Salandit.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: It punishes Salandit that couldn’t bring it food with a fierce slap of its flame-spewing palm.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: Salazzle lives deep in caves and forces the Salandit it has attracted with its pheromones to serve it.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: Filled with pheromones, its poisonous gas can be diluted to use in the production of luscious perfumes.

Name: Salazzle
FlavorText: For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: A Greedent drawn in by the sweet scent of these Pokémon will tuck the Bounsweet in among the berries in its tail and carry them all away.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled-down fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in the past, when sweeteners were scarce.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: When under attack, it secretes a sweet and delicious sweat. The scent only calls more enemies to it.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: Its body gives off a sweet, fruity scent that is extremely appetizing to bird Pokémon.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: It tries to resist being swallowed by a bird Pokémon by spinning the sepals on its head. It’s usually a fruitless attempt.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: Because of its sweet, delicious aroma, bird Pokémon are always after it, but it’s not intelligent enough to care.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: Although it’s too sugary for human consumption, Bounsweet’s sweat can be watered down into a juice with just the right amount of sweetness.

Name: Bounsweet
FlavorText: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by Toucannon lured by that wafting deliciousness.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: Steenee bounces energetically through forests. If the rind that peels off its body is pulverized, it can be used to treat stomach pains.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: Steenee spreads a sweet scent that makes others feel invigorated. This same scent is popular for antiperspirants.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: Any Corvisquire that pecks at this Pokémon will be greeted with a smack from its sepals followed by a sharp kick.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: As it twirls like a dancer, a sweet smell spreads out around it. Anyone who inhales the scent will feel a surge of happiness.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: It bounces around, swinging the sepals on its head with abandon. They’re quite painful when they smack you!

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: It’s protected by its hard sepals, so it plays with bird Pokémon without worry. They peck it relentlessly, but it doesn’t care.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: This Pokémon is always bouncing around energetically. Other Pokémon are attracted by its lively appearance and pleasant aroma.

Name: Steenee
FlavorText: The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: This Pokémon launches fierce yet elegant kicks with its long, slender legs. It views Quaquaval as its rival.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: This Pokémon is proud and aggressive. However, it is said that a Tsareena will instantly become calm if someone touches the crown on its calyx.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: A kick from the hardened tips of this Pokémon’s legs leaves a wound in the opponent’s body and soul that will never heal.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: This feared Pokémon has long, slender legs and a cruel heart. It shows no mercy as it stomps on its opponents.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: A Pokémon with an aggressive personality and a mastery of kicking, it cackles every time it kicks an opponent.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: A master of grand and beautiful kicks, it can knock out even kickboxing champions with a single blow.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: A Pokémon known for the beauty of its well-shaped legs, it sometimes appears as a mascot in advertisements for beauty salons.

Name: Tsareena
FlavorText: Its long, striking legs aren’t just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.

Name: Wimpod
FlavorText: Wimpod gather in swarms, constantly on the lookout for danger. They scatter the moment they detect an enemy’s presence.

Name: Wimpod
FlavorText: It’s nature’s cleaner—it eats anything and everything, including garbage and rotten things. The ground near its nest is always clean.

Name: Wimpod
FlavorText: An astonishingly cowardly Pokémon, Wimpod will whir its legs at high speeds to run away if anything comes near it.

Name: Wimpod
FlavorText: It will pick up anything it finds on the ground. Sometimes it finds coins, so Murkrow and Meowth will go after it.

Name: Wimpod
FlavorText: Its habitat varies from beaches to seabeds. A natural scavenger, it will gleefully chow down on anything edible, no matter how rotten.

Name: Wimpod
FlavorText: This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.

Name: Golisopod
FlavorText: They live in sunken ships or in holes in the seabed. When Golisopod and Grapploct battle, the loser becomes the winner’s meal.

Name: Golisopod
FlavorText: It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.

Name: Golisopod
FlavorText: Its claws, which it can extend and retract at will, are its greatest weapons. Golisopod is sometimes accompanied by Wimpod.

Name: Golisopod
FlavorText: The shell covering its body is as hard as diamond. This Pokémon will do anything it takes to win.

Name: Golisopod
FlavorText: It battles skillfully with its six arms, but spends most of its time peacefully meditating in caves deep beneath the sea.

Name: Golisopod
FlavorText: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.

Name: Pyukumuku
FlavorText: It’s covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist, allowing it to stay on land for days without drying up.

Name: Pyukumuku
FlavorText: It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.

Name: Pyukumuku
FlavorText: Its entire body is covered in its own slime. If you accidentally step on one, you’ll slip, and it will get mad and smack you!

Name: Pyukumuku
FlavorText: The tradition known as Pyukumuku chucking started from the custom of throwing Pyukumuku back into the sea after they wash onshore.

Name: Pyukumuku
FlavorText: These Pokémon line the beaches. The sticky mucous that covers their bodies can be used to soothe sunburned skin. How convenient!

Name: Pyukumuku
FlavorText: It lives in shallow seas, such as areas near a beach. It can eject its internal organs, which it uses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.

Name: Turtonator
FlavorText: Eating sulfur in its volcanic habitat is what causes explosive compounds to develop in its shell. Its droppings are also dangerously explosive.

Name: Turtonator
FlavorText: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.

Name: Turtonator
FlavorText: Its exploding shell poses a real danger but is sensitive to moisture. On rainy days, Turtonator takes silent refuge in caves.

Name: Turtonator
FlavorText: It lives in volcanoes and eats sulfur and other minerals. Materials from the food it eats form the basis of its explosive shell.

Name: Turtonator
FlavorText: It gushes fire and poisonous gases from its nostrils. Its dung is an explosive substance and can be put to various uses.

Name: Turtonator
FlavorText: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.

Name: Bruxish
FlavorText: When sunlight reflects on the ripples created by a Bruxish grinding its teeth, the water all around sparkles brilliantly.

Name: Bruxish
FlavorText: It grinds its teeth with great force to stimulate its brain. It fires the psychic energy created by this process from the protuberance on its head.

Name: Bruxish
FlavorText: Its skin is thick enough to fend off Mareanie’s spikes. With its robust teeth, Bruxish crunches up the spikes and eats them.

Name: Bruxish
FlavorText: It burrows beneath the sand, radiating psychic power from the protuberance on its head. It waits for prey as it surveys the area.

Name: Bruxish
FlavorText: It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth. Even Shellder’s shell is no match for it.

Name: Bruxish
FlavorText: When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the grating sound of grinding teeth echoes through the area.

Name: Dhelmise
FlavorText: After lowering its anchor, it waits for its prey. It catches large Wailord and drains their life-force.

Name: Dhelmise
FlavorText: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.

Name: Dhelmise
FlavorText: Its chain-like green seaweed can stretch outward for hundreds of yards. For some reason, it gets along well with Skrelp.

Name: Dhelmise
FlavorText: It wraps its prey in green seaweed and sucks away their vitality. It only likes to go after big prey like Wailord.

Name: Dhelmise
FlavorText: The soul of seaweed adrift in the waves became reborn as this Pokémon. It maintains itself with new infusions of seabed detritus and seaweed.

Name: Dhelmise
FlavorText: Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord in a single blow. What appears to be green seaweed is actually its body.

Name: Tapu Bulu
FlavorText: It makes ringing sounds with its tail to let others know where it is, avoiding unneeded conflicts. This guardian deity of Ula’ula controls plants.

Name: Tapu Bulu
FlavorText: Although it’s called a guardian deity, it’s violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

Name: Tapu Bulu
FlavorText: The guardian deity of Ula’ula is a lazy Pokémon. It commands plants to immobilize its foes and then deals them a savage blow with its horns.

Name: Tapu Bulu
FlavorText: It pulls large trees up by the roots and swings them around. It causes vegetation to grow, and then it absorbs energy from the growth.

Name: Tapu Fini
FlavorText: Although it’s called a guardian deity, terrible calamities sometimes befall those who recklessly approach Tapu Fini.

Name: Tapu Fini
FlavorText: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.

Name: Tapu Fini
FlavorText: The guardian deity of Poni, it can control water. People say it can create pure water that will wash away any uncleanness.

Name: Tapu Fini
FlavorText: The dense fog it creates brings the downfall and destruction of its confused enemies. Ocean currents are the source of its energy.

Name: Kartana
FlavorText: This Ultra Beast’s body, which is as thin as paper, is like a sharpened sword.

Name: Kartana
FlavorText: One of the Ultra Beast life-forms, it was observed cutting down a gigantic steel tower with one stroke of its blade.

Name: Kartana
FlavorText: This Ultra Beast came from the Ultra Wormhole. It seems not to attack enemies on its own, but its sharp body is a dangerous weapon in itself.

Name: Blacephalon
FlavorText: A UB that appeared from an Ultra Wormhole, it causes explosions, then takes advantage of opponents’ surprise to rob them of their vitality.

Name: Blacephalon
FlavorText: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

Name: Grookey
FlavorText: It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.

Name: Grookey
FlavorText: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

Name: Thwackey
FlavorText: When it’s drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won’t even notice that it’s already knocked out its opponent.

Name: Thwackey
FlavorText: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.

Name: Rillaboom
FlavorText: Rillaboom has become one with its forest of drums and continues to lay down beats that shake all of Galar.

Name: Rillaboom
FlavorText: Gigantamax energy has caused Rillaboom’s stump to grow into a drum set that resembles a forest.

Name: Rillaboom
FlavorText: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.

Name: Rillaboom
FlavorText: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

Name: Scorbunny
FlavorText: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it’s raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.

Name: Scorbunny
FlavorText: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon’s body. Once that happens, it’s ready to fight at full power.

Name: Raboot
FlavorText: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.

Name: Raboot
FlavorText: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves.

Name: Cinderace
FlavorText: Gigantamax energy can sometimes cause the diameter of this Pokémon’s fireball to exceed 300 feet.

Name: Cinderace
FlavorText: Infused with Cinderace’s fighting spirit, the gigantic Pyro Ball never misses its targets and completely roasts opponents.

Name: Cinderace
FlavorText: It’s skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

Name: Cinderace
FlavorText: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.

Name: Sobble
FlavorText: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.

Name: Sobble
FlavorText: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won’t be able to resist weeping.

Name: Drizzile
FlavorText: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.

Name: Drizzile
FlavorText: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.

Name: Inteleon
FlavorText: It has excellent sniping skills. Shooting a berry rolling along over nine miles away is a piece of cake for this Pokémon.

Name: Inteleon
FlavorText: Gigantamax Inteleon’s Water Gun move fires at Mach 7. As the Pokémon takes aim, it uses the crest on its head to gauge wind and temperature.

Name: Inteleon
FlavorText: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes’ weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.

Name: Inteleon
FlavorText: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

Name: Gossifleur
FlavorText: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.

Name: Gossifleur
FlavorText: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

Name: Eldegoss
FlavorText: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.

Name: Eldegoss
FlavorText: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

Name: Chewtle
FlavorText: A popular game among children is to lift up sticks that Chewtle have bitten onto to see whose Chewtle can hang on the longest.

Name: Chewtle
FlavorText: Its large front tooth is still growing in. When the tooth itches, this Pokémon will bite another Chewtle’s horn, and the two Pokémon will tussle.

Name: Chewtle
FlavorText: It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.

Name: Chewtle
FlavorText: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.

Name: Drednaw
FlavorText: In the Galar region, there’s a tale about this Pokémon chewing up a mountain and using the rubble to stop a flood.

Name: Drednaw
FlavorText: It responded to Gigantamax energy by becoming bipedal. First it comes crashing down on foes, and then it finishes them off with its massive jaws.

Name: Drednaw
FlavorText: Drednaw lurks along the shoreline. When prey come to drink water, Drednaw stretches its neck out and chomps down on them.

Name: Drednaw
FlavorText: Its massive, jagged teeth can crush a boulder in a single bite. This Pokémon has an extremely vicious disposition.

Name: Drednaw
FlavorText: This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.

Name: Drednaw
FlavorText: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

Name: Carkol
FlavorText: Due to the coal tar created inside it, the heap of coal on Carkol’s back never falls apart, even when the Pokémon rolls around at high speeds.

Name: Carkol
FlavorText: The temperature inside its body increases when it experiences strong emotions. It rolls around frantically while spewing flames.

Name: Carkol
FlavorText: By rapidly rolling its legs, it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Carkol
FlavorText: It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.

Name: Coalossal
FlavorText: When Galar was hit by a harsh cold wave, this Pokémon served as a giant heating stove and saved many lives.

Name: Coalossal
FlavorText: Its body is a colossal stove. With Gigantamax energy stoking the fire, this Pokémon’s flame burns hotter than 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Coalossal
FlavorText: It’s gentle usually but fearsome when angered. With a body that burns at over 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit, it crushes foes and turns them to ash.

Name: Coalossal
FlavorText: To intimidate its opponents, Coalossal will vigorously shake its body, scattering coal from its smoldering back.

Name: Coalossal
FlavorText: While it’s engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.

Name: Coalossal
FlavorText: It’s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Applin
FlavorText: Applin lives inside an apple. When an Applin is separated from its apple, its body loses moisture and the Pokémon grows weak.

Name: Applin
FlavorText: It grows by eating the flesh of an apple. Applin uses its own body fluid to strengthen the apple’s skin and prevent it from rotting.

Name: Applin
FlavorText: As soon as it’s born, it burrows into an apple. Not only does the apple serve as its food source, but the flavor of the fruit determines its evolution.

Name: Applin
FlavorText: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it’s just an apple and nothing more.

Name: Flapple
FlavorText: If it stretches its neck, the strong aroma of its nectar pours out. The scent is so sickeningly sweet that one whiff makes other Pokémon faint.

Name: Flapple
FlavorText: Under the influence of Gigantamax energy, it produces much more sweet nectar, and its shape has changed to resemble a giant apple.

Name: Flapple
FlavorText: It uses its own body fluid to repair its apple. Strong Flapple that have won many battles have apples that are clay colored all over.

Name: Flapple
FlavorText: It flutters around while seeking an opening in the opponent’s guard, then attacks by spitting acidic liquid strong enough to melt metal.

Name: Flapple
FlavorText: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.

Name: Flapple
FlavorText: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.

Name: Appletun
FlavorText: Due to Gigantamax energy, this Pokémon’s nectar has thickened. The increased viscosity lets the nectar absorb more damage than before.

Name: Appletun
FlavorText: It blasts its opponents with massive amounts of sweet, sticky nectar, drowning them under the deluge.

Name: Appletun
FlavorText: When some Lechonk come along to lick the sweet nectar on Appletun’s back, Appletun will spew sticky nectar at them to drive them away.

Name: Appletun
FlavorText: It feeds mainly on sweet apples. It will also eat small bug Pokémon that are attracted by its sweet nectar.

Name: Appletun
FlavorText: Its body is covered in sweet nectar, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.

Name: Appletun
FlavorText: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.

Name: Cramorant
FlavorText: The slightest shock is sometimes enough to get this Pokémon to spit out the Arrokuda lodged in its throat.

Name: Cramorant
FlavorText: Cramorant’s gluttony led it to try to swallow an Arrokuda whole, which in turn led to Cramorant getting an Arrokuda stuck in its throat.

Name: Cramorant
FlavorText: The half-swallowed Pikachu is so startled that it isn’t struggling yet, but it’s still looking for a chance to strike back.

Name: Cramorant
FlavorText: This Cramorant has accidentally gotten a Pikachu lodged in its gullet. Cramorant is choking a little, but it isn’t really bothered.

Name: Cramorant
FlavorText: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.

Name: Cramorant
FlavorText: It’s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it’s battling midfight.

Name: Arrokuda
FlavorText: It takes down prey by charging into them with its hard, pointed jaw. But Arrokuda’s eyesight is poor, so this tactic has a low success rate.

Name: Arrokuda
FlavorText: Arrokuda can swim quickly only in a straight line. The ones that become sluggish from overeating are the first to be targeted by flocks of Wattrel.

Name: Arrokuda
FlavorText: After it’s eaten its fill, its movements become extremely sluggish. That’s when Cramorant swallows it up.

Name: Arrokuda
FlavorText: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It’s very proud of that jaw.

Name: Barraskewda
FlavorText: It swims at speeds of over 100 knots and battles fiercely with pods of Finizen over prey.

Name: Barraskewda
FlavorText: It spins its tail fins to leap from the water, then viciously bites down on Wingull flying close to the water’s surface.

Name: Barraskewda
FlavorText: It spins its tail fins to propel itself, surging forward at speeds of over 100 knots before ramming prey and spearing into them.

Name: Barraskewda
FlavorText: This Pokémon has a jaw that’s as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda’s flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.

Name: Sizzlipede
FlavorText: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they’re well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.

Name: Sizzlipede
FlavorText: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

Name: Centiskorch
FlavorText: The heat that comes off a Gigantamax Centiskorch may destabilize air currents. Sometimes it can even cause storms.

Name: Centiskorch
FlavorText: Gigantamax energy has evoked a rise in its body temperature, now reaching over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. Its heat waves incinerate its enemies.

Name: Centiskorch
FlavorText: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.

Name: Centiskorch
FlavorText: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

Name: Dracovish
FlavorText: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph, but this Pokémon can’t breathe unless it’s underwater.

Name: Dracovish
FlavorText: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.

Name: Arctovish
FlavorText: The skin on its face is impervious to attack, but breathing difficulties made this Pokémon go extinct anyway.

Name: Arctovish
FlavorText: Though it’s able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.

Name: Urshifu
FlavorText: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in defeating foes by raining many blows down on them. Its strikes are nonstop, flowing like a river.

Name: Urshifu
FlavorText: It’s believed that this Pokémon modeled its fighting style on the flow of a river—sometimes rapid, sometimes calm.

Name: Urshifu
FlavorText: All it takes is a glare from this Pokémon to take the lives of those with evil in their hearts—or so they say.

Name: Urshifu
FlavorText: As it waits for the right moment to unleash its Gigantamax power, this Pokémon maintains a perfect one-legged stance. It won’t even twitch.

Name: Zarude
FlavorText: This Zarude’s special strength stems from its love and care for an orphaned human child that the Pokémon has raised since the child’s infancy.

Name: Zarude
FlavorText: This Zarude left its pack to raise a human child. The cloth Zarude would wrap the child with has a comforting scent that calmed the child’s crying.

Name: Zarude
FlavorText: Once the vines on Zarude’s body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.

Name: Zarude
FlavorText: Within dense forests, this Pokémon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It’s incredibly aggressive, and the other Pokémon of the forest fear it.

Name: Calyrex
FlavorText: Calyrex is known in legend as a king that ruled over Galar in ancient times. It has the power to cause hearts to mend and plants to spring forth.

Name: Calyrex
FlavorText: Calyrex is a merciful Pokémon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.

Name: Basculegion
FlavorText: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui’s rivers is Basculegion’s equal.

Name: Sprigatito
FlavorText: The sweet scent its body gives off mesmerizes those around it. The scent grows stronger when this Pokémon is in the sun.

Name: Sprigatito
FlavorText: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

Name: Floragato
FlavorText: The hardness of Floragato’s fur depends on the Pokémon’s mood. When Floragato is prepared to battle, its fur becomes pointed and needle sharp.

Name: Floragato
FlavorText: Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against its opponents.

Name: Meowscarada
FlavorText: With skillful misdirection, it rigs foes with pollen-packed flower bombs. Meowscarada sets off the bombs before its foes realize what’s going on.

Name: Meowscarada
FlavorText: This Pokémon uses the reflective fur lining its cape to camouflage the stem of its flower, creating the illusion that the flower is floating.

Name: Fuecoco
FlavorText: Its flame sac is small, so energy is always leaking out. This energy is released from the dent atop Fuecoco’s head and flickers to and fro.

Name: Fuecoco
FlavorText: It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.

Name: Crocalor
FlavorText: The valve in Crocalor’s flame sac is closely connected to its vocal cords. This Pokémon utters a guttural cry as it spews flames every which way.

Name: Crocalor
FlavorText: The combination of Crocalor’s fire energy and overflowing vitality has caused an egg-shaped fireball to appear on the Pokémon’s head.

Name: Skeledirge
FlavorText: Skeledirge’s gentle singing soothes the souls of all that hear it. It burns its enemies to a crisp with flames of over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Skeledirge
FlavorText: The fiery bird changes shape when Skeledirge sings. Rumor has it that the bird was born when the fireball on Skeledirge’s head gained a soul.

Name: Quaxly
FlavorText: Its strong legs let it easily swim around in even fast-flowing rivers. It likes to keep things tidy and is prone to overthinking things.

Name: Quaxly
FlavorText: This Pokémon migrated to Paldea from distant lands long ago. The gel secreted by its feathers repels water and grime.

Name: Quaxwell
FlavorText: The hardworking Quaxwell observes people and Pokémon from various regions and incorporates their movements into its own dance routines.

Name: Quaxwell
FlavorText: These Pokémon constantly run through shallow waters to train their legs, then compete with each other to see which of them kicks most gracefully.

Name: Quaquaval
FlavorText: Dancing in ways that evoke far-away places, this Pokémon mesmerizes all that see it. Flourishes of its decorative water feathers slice into its foes.

Name: Quaquaval
FlavorText: A single kick from a Quaquaval can send a truck rolling. This Pokémon uses its powerful legs to perform striking dances from far-off lands.

Name: Smoliv
FlavorText: This Pokémon converts nutrients into oil, which it stores in the fruit on its head. It can easily go a whole week without eating or drinking.

Name: Smoliv
FlavorText: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

Name: Dolliv
FlavorText: It basks in the sun to its heart’s content until the fruits on its head ripen. After that, Dolliv departs from human settlements and goes on a journey.

Name: Dolliv
FlavorText: Dolliv shares its tasty, fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.

Name: Arboliva
FlavorText: This Pokémon drives back enemies by launching its rich, aromatic oil at them with enough force to smash a boulder.

Name: Arboliva
FlavorText: This calm Pokémon is very compassionate. It will share its delicious, nutrient-rich oil with weakened Pokémon.

Name: Charcadet
FlavorText: Its firepower increases when it fights, reaching over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit. It likes berries that are rich in fat.

Name: Charcadet
FlavorText: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

Name: Armarouge
FlavorText: This Pokémon clads itself in armor that has been fortified by psychic and fire energy, and it shoots blazing fireballs.

Name: Armarouge
FlavorText: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokémon is incredibly loyal.

Name: Ceruledge
FlavorText: An old set of armor steeped in grudges caused this Pokémon’s evolution. Ceruledge cuts its enemies to pieces without mercy.

Name: Ceruledge
FlavorText: The fiery blades on its arms burn fiercely with the lingering resentment of a sword wielder who fell before accomplishing their goal.

Name: Bramblin
FlavorText: Not even Bramblin knows where it is headed as it tumbles across the wilderness, blown by the wind. It loathes getting wet.

Name: Bramblin
FlavorText: A soul unable to move on to the afterlife was blown around by the wind until it got tangled up with dried grass and became a Pokémon.

Name: Brambleghast
FlavorText: Brambleghast wanders around arid regions. On rare occasions, mass outbreaks of these Pokémon will bury an entire town.

Name: Brambleghast
FlavorText: It will open the branches of its head to envelop its prey. Once it absorbs all the life energy it needs, it expels the prey and discards it.

Name: Toedscool
FlavorText: Though it looks like Tentacool, Toedscool is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.

Name: Toedscool
FlavorText: Toedscool lives in muggy forests. The flaps that fall from its body are chewy and very delicious.

Name: Toedscruel
FlavorText: It coils its 10 tentacles around prey and sucks out their nutrients, causing the prey pain. The folds along the rim of its head are a popular delicacy.

Name: Toedscruel
FlavorText: These Pokémon gather into groups and form colonies deep within forests. They absolutely hate it when strangers approach.

Name: Capsakid
FlavorText: Traditional Paldean dishes can be extremely spicy because they include the shed front teeth of Capsakid among their ingredients.

Name: Capsakid
FlavorText: The more sunlight this Pokémon bathes in, the more spicy chemicals are produced by its body, and thus the spicier its moves become.

Name: Wiglett
FlavorText: Though it looks like Diglett, Wiglett is an entirely different species. The resemblance seems to be a coincidental result of environmental adaptation.

Name: Wiglett
FlavorText: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

Name: Wugtrio
FlavorText: A variety of fish Pokémon, Wugtrio was once considered to be a regional form of Dugtrio.

Name: Wugtrio
FlavorText: It has a vicious temperament, contrary to what its appearance may suggest. It wraps its long bodies around prey, then drags the prey into its den.

Name: Finizen
FlavorText: Its water ring is made from seawater mixed with a sticky fluid that Finizen secretes from its blowhole.

Name: Finizen
FlavorText: It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.

Name: Palafin
FlavorText: This hero of the ocean swims at a speed of 50 knots and saves drowning people and Pokémon.

Name: Palafin
FlavorText: This Pokémon’s ancient genes have awakened. It is now so extraordinarily strong that it can easily lift a cruise ship with one fin.

Name: Palafin
FlavorText: Its physical capabilities are no different than a Finizen’s, but when its allies are in danger, it transforms and powers itself up.

Name: Palafin
FlavorText: This Pokémon changes its appearance if it hears its allies calling for help. Palafin will never show anybody its moment of transformation.

Name: Veluza
FlavorText: Veluza has excellent regenerative capabilities. It sheds spare flesh from its body to boost its agility, then charges at its prey.

Name: Veluza
FlavorText: When Veluza discards unnecessary flesh, its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. The spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.

Name: Dondozo
FlavorText: It treats Tatsugiri like its boss and follows it loyally. Though powerful, Dondozo is apparently not very smart.

Name: Dondozo
FlavorText: This Pokémon is a glutton, but it’s bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.

Name: Tatsugiri
FlavorText: It’s one of the most intelligent dragon Pokémon. It camouflages itself by inflating its throat sac.

Name: Tatsugiri
FlavorText: Bird Pokémon are its main prey. This Pokémon knows it’s weak, so it hunts with a partner.

Name: Tatsugiri
FlavorText: This Pokémon tricks its opponents by playing dead. It is small and weak, but it uses its smarts to survive.

Name: Tatsugiri
FlavorText: This species’ differing colors and patterns are apparently the result of Tatsugiri changing itself to suit the preferences of the prey it lures in.

Name: Tatsugiri
FlavorText: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

Name: Tatsugiri
FlavorText: This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies on the outside.

Name: Brute Bonnet
FlavorText: It bears a slight resemblance to a Pokémon described in a dubious magazine as a cross between a dinosaur and a mushroom.

Name: Brute Bonnet
FlavorText: It is possible that the creature listed as Brute Bonnet in a certain book could actually be this Pokémon.

Name: Iron Bundle
FlavorText: It resembles a mysterious object mentioned in an old book. There are only two reported sightings of this Pokémon.

Name: Iron Bundle
FlavorText: Its shape is similar to a robot featured in a paranormal magazine article. The robot was said to have been created by an ancient civilization.

Name: Iron Moth
FlavorText: No records exist of this species being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with an object described in an old book.

Name: Iron Moth
FlavorText: This Pokémon resembles an unknown object described in a paranormal magazine as a UFO sent to observe humanity.

Name: Wo-Chien
FlavorText: It drains the life-force from vegetation, causing nearby forests to instantly wither and fields to turn barren.

Name: Wo-Chien
FlavorText: The grudge of a person punished for writing the king’s evil deeds upon wooden tablets has clad itself in dead leaves to become a Pokémon.

Name: Chi-Yu
FlavorText: The envy accumulated within curved beads that sparked multiple conflicts has clad itself in fire and become a Pokémon.

Name: Chi-Yu
FlavorText: It controls flames burning at over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit. It casually swims through the sea of lava it creates by melting rock and sand.
